UID:5f91f647b5f5fe6cb8553a2b14d06a79122026_10:38:49_AM@campusgroups.com
SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:George Mason Call of Duty Spring 2026 Tryouts
LOCATION: Sign in to download the location
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2292001
DESCRIPTION:ATTENTION ALL COD PLAYERS!\nTryouts are on the horizon, and you need to get ready for this opportunity to join one of the most competitive teams at GMU!\n\n🔒 Team Requirements:\n-YOU MUST BE A FULL-TIME STUDENT AT GEORGE MASON UNIVERSITY! This requires you to take a minimum of 12 credits, if you are not taking 12 credits you will not be accepted.\n-Must be available 2-3 times a week for scheduled practices/games (most often later in the day)\n-Must be able to communicate effectively in voice chat\n-Must follow the player contracts given to the players.\n-Must be IN CALL and communicating 15-30 minutes before official matches\n-Schedule conflicts are your responsibility to reschedule matches with your teammates.\n-Repeated tardiness/lack of communication about rescheduling (3 minor/1 major) will lead to benching/removal from the team.\n-Call of duty leagues require CONTROLLER ONLY. Thus, player on keyboard and mouse who do not switch will not be accepted. CONTROLLERS WILL NOT BE PROVIDED.\n-Some competitive leagues require you to play in-person, keep that in mind. \n\n🗒️ Team Information:\nGMU Patriots: Premier or "Varsity" Competitive Team, composed of Crim+ Players with lots of COD Experience, and are expected to qualify for ALL major events.\nGMU Academy: Non-Premier or "Junior Varsity" competitive, composed of Gold, Plat+ Players.\nhttps://discord.gg/Z3fjCGMu\n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2292001
END:VEVENT
