UID:4d80cdd513efb5c02eafd1eafcc2fb669302025_11:28:54_AM@campusgroups.com
SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:"How to Learn" Workshop Series 
LOCATION:Horizon Hall, Room 2008, 4400 University Drive, MSN 2C4, Fairfax, VA 22030, United States
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2289360
DESCRIPTION:Please register for each session you plan to attend. Participants are welcome to bring snacks and beverages to the sessions. FREE LUNCH provided.\n\nAbout This Event\n\nKick off your semester with a supportive and skill-building workshop designed to help you study more effectively and confidently. During How to Learn, you’ll explore research-based strategies that strengthen focus, boost memory, and enhance long-term retention. Whether you’re looking to improve time management, develop better study habits, or prepare for upcoming exams, this event provides structured guidance and practical tools you can start using immediately.\n\nOur sessions include interactive activities, real-world examples, and opportunities to practice techniques that top students rely on. You’ll also have the chance to meet with an academic coach for individualized feedback tailored to your learning needs.\n\nThis workshop series is ideal for any student—new, returning, undergraduate, or graduate—who wants to enter the semester organized, motivated, and equipped for success. Plus, enjoy a welcoming environment, free lunch, and a chance to connect with peers.\n\nWe look forward to supporting your academic journey and helping you start strong!\n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2289360
END:VEVENT
