UID:3caf9c29b2285ed26846324adcf55947152026_10:14:38_PM@campusgroups.com
SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:Alpha Kappa Psi Family Feud (Rush Week Day #2) 
LOCATION:Johnson Center Room 239A, 4400 University Drive, MSN 2D6 Mailbox 136, Fairfax, VA 22030, United States
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2292082
DESCRIPTION:The second event of Rush Week will be a Family Feud style game. This event will consist of PNMs and Brothers being placed in multiple “families”, or groups (ratio dependent on amount of people, likely groups of five total). After a brief 3-5 minute introduction, each family will work together to figure out the most popular answers to survey questions given by AKPsi Brothers. These questions would be a mix of fun and business-related. To play, the host reads the first question aloud. Then, a member of the first team (rotates each round) has five seconds to confer and give their answer. Families earn points by matching the most common responses. The winner of this game would be the family who assumed the most points after 10 questions. \n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2292082
END:VEVENT
