SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:Ecuador Summer 2026 Study Abroad -- Sustainable Futures: A Case Study of Quito and Galápagos (COPY)
LOCATION:Online Event
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2293457
DESCRIPTION:This two-week course examines how sustainability intersects with governance, inequality, indigenous rights, and urban development in one of Latin America's most ecologically and culturally diverse countries. Students will spend the first 1.5 weeks on the scenic Cumbayá campus of the Universidad San Francisco de Quito (USFQ), engaging in morning seminars with local scholars and afternoon site visits to National Parks and field stations. After this, students will take an unforgettable trip to the uniquely historic and biodiverse Galápagos Islands, the inspiration for Charles Darwin's theory of evolution. \n\nMeeting Link: https://gmu.zoom.us/j/6101383264?pwd=Jsa6aHjaaAfTVKkoereJNqg2x15aCw.1\nDress Code: Casual (jeans ok)\n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2293457
END:VEVENT
