UID:44bebe0f7dce29ab581ae9ba9552f8a51222026_1:23:49_PM@campusgroups.com
SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:Venice Biennale Art and Art History - Summer Study Abroad
LOCATION:Online Event
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2293873
DESCRIPTION:Come learn about this amazing study abroad opportunity in Venice, Italy. This course examines twenty-first century contemporary art through participation in the 61st Venice Biennale, the most celebrated global display of art attended by artists, collectors, curators, and art historians all over the world. Each nation selects works from its most up-and-coming artists, which are displayed all over the city of Venice. The historic 2026 Biennale is the first time that a Black African female scholar was selected to curate and there will be an emphasis on art of the African diaspora and the Global South, as well as how the African presence in Venice has shaped the city’s history and culture.  In addition to viewing and discussing these wide-ranging art displays, the program includes museum visits, guided city tours, a glassblowing studio visit, a catamaran cruise, and a day trip to Padua, plus free days and weekends for you to explore Venice and travel to other cities in Italy and beyond. \n\nMeeting Link: https://gmu.zoom.us/j/6101383264?pwd=Jsa6aHjaaAfTVKkoereJNqg2x15aCw.1\nDress Code: Casual (jeans ok)\n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2293873
END:VEVENT
