UID:6ce7c9e2345b36c88e65abe7772b8f141112026_3:54:30_PM@campusgroups.com
SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:Woodland and River Trail Loop
LOCATION:Woodland and River Trail Loop
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2292386
DESCRIPTION:This trail is rated as moderate on AllTrails. Woodland and River Trail Loop in Scotts Run Stream Valley Park is a scenic and nature-rich hike featuring river views, a small waterfall, wildflowers, and historic ruins. The loop winds through mature hardwood forest with towering oak, beech, hemlock, and wild cherry trees, creating a peaceful woodland atmosphere. In the spring, the area is especially popular for its seasonal wildflowers, including Virginia bluebells, trillium, and trailing arbutus that bloom along the hillsides. While the trail is mostly easy to follow, hikers should expect a few short but steep sections near the river. Downloading the map ahead of time is recommended.\n\nLength: 2.5 miles\nElevation gain: 291 ft\nEstimated duration: 1 – 1.5 hours + driving time\n\nIf you plan to join, please mark yourself as “Interested” or “Going” on the event so we can plan accordingly!\n\nJoin the Discord to get updates on the meeting time and location before the hike:\nhttps://discord.gg/YExq6kj5ZU\nDress Code: Casual (jeans ok)\n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2292386
END:VEVENT
