UID:37e85192318d5f8fb2e1abdbe47b1b641142026_9:53:42_AM@campusgroups.com
SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:Info Session - Study Abroad: Media and Culture in Japan
LOCATION:Art and Design Building, Room 2002, 38.82791077679879,-77.30632822704045
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2292518
DESCRIPTION:Japan's animation, games, electronics and film, along with their artistic styles, have deeply influenced the world's media and cultural landscape for over 75 years. Discover everything, from the ancient origins to the cutting edge of Japan's popular culture and media, with a two-week journey through the country's creative capitals.\n\nhttps://masonabroad.gmu.edu/index.cfm?FuseAction=Programs.ViewProgramAngular&id=10786\n\nLed by game designer and former resident of Japan Prof. Josiah Lebowitz, you'll:\n\n•	Learn about Japanese game, anime, and manga development from professionals and your own research and observation.\n•	Gain insight into how games, anime, manga, and other media are marketed and sold in Japan and abroad.\n•	Develop a better understanding of the role you could play in international game and media development!\n\nDon't miss out on this amazing opportunity to earn academic credit while unravelling one of the world's most influential media landscapes. Join us on February 2 at 9:30 AM in room in the Art & Design Building Room 2002 to ask questions, seek clarification, or just learn a little about this exciting opportunity. The Information session is open to everyone.\n\nHope to see you there!\nDress Code: Casual (jeans ok)\n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2292518
END:VEVENT
