UID:b046df87fa0d50ada7e19f870bc1130512102025_3:20:16_PM@campusgroups.com
SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:Homecoming Day of Service
LOCATION:The NEW Activities Building and various other locations TBD, United States
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2291844
DESCRIPTION:Serve your campus and your community with multiple service projects across campus, including the INOVA Blood Drive, Stuff-a-Truck Donation Drive, Flower Pot decorating, and Snack Packs for Kids! Part of Homecoming Team Competition, registered teams that participate will earn points towards a cash prize. You do not have to be a part of a team to participate. \n\nInformation about Team Competition rules available at https://homecoming.gmu.edu/team-competition-updates/\n\n10am - 4pm Projects\n\nINOVA Blood Drive -  Sign up here: https://bit.ly/GMU0204\n\nDid you know that just 1 blood donation can save up to 3 lives and that the average red blood cell transfusion is 3 pints (or 3 whole-blood donations)? More than 1 million people every year are diagnosed with cancer for the first time, and many of them will need blood—sometimes daily—during chemotherapy. More than 38,000 blood donations are needed every day, and while 38% of the American population is eligible, only 2% actually donate.\n\nStuff-a-Truck Donation Drive - Wish list can be found here: https://www.amazon.com/gp/registry/wishlist/3W1RAZSSCJM5/ref=pdp_new_wl?\n\nThe SI2Go Truck will be parked outside the Activities Building to accept food and supply donations for our chosen charities. This year, items will be donated to the Patriot Pantry, George Mason’s own food pantry for students experiencing food insecurity, or to Food for Others, a food pantry serving individuals and families in Fairfax County.\n\n11am - 1pm Projects\n\nChew toys \nVolunteers will make chew toys for animals using fleece. Chew toys will be donated to a local area animal shelter.\n\nFlowerpots  \nBring the green and gold spirit to our very own Campus Gardens by helping to decorate flowerpots!\n\nSnack Bag Packing\nIn partnership with Van Metre, we will be filling bags with food items for students facing food insecurity a local area elementary school. Volunteers will be working directly with 4th-5th grade students from Pattie Elementary.\n\nColor a smile  \nJoin us as we help to spread smiles with cheerful drawings. Color A Smile is a nonprofit organization that distributes cheerful drawings to senior citizens, our troops overseas, and anyone in need of a smile. Every month we mail thousands of new drawings to the recipients on our mailing list. Since 1990, Color A Smile has given out millions of cheerful drawings. That’s a lot of smiles!\n\nPats for Patriots \nVolunteers will help submit Pats for Patriots to thank, recognize, show appreciation for a Mason colleague or student who has taken the time to do something kind, generous or thoughtful towards others. \nGOAL: 100 Pats\n\nMaintain Mason Projects\n10am-11am\n3pm-4pm\n\nJoin Student Government for a special Homecoming edition of Maintain Mason! Maintain Mason is a Student Government tradition to keep our campus clean and sustainable by picking up trash. Please dress comfortably! Gloves and grabbers provided. Meet at the Activities Building.\n\nPresident's Park Greenhouse Project\n\nJoin us at the Presidents Park Greenhouse to help harvest baby salad greens, tomatoes, and lettuce, then package them for donation. Other tasks may include cleaning and maintenance of the hydroponic systems and greenhouse.\n\nLOCATION: The Presidents Park Greenhouse is located between Ike’s Dining Hall and Taylor Hall, near Robert's Road, at 10444 Presidents Park Dr. and is shown as #26 on the right/eastern side of the campus map. Feel free to call the manager, Doni, at 703-993-4220, if you have trouble finding the greenhouse. Spaces are limited! Register here: https://gmufacilities.knack.com/sustainability-volunteer#my-events/view-event-details/5ce2b0c47c850d0006ab026e/\n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2291844
END:VEVENT
