UID:b12bb8c04e22e1e4cf878ecd685c2c521262026_7:55:20_PM@campusgroups.com
SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:Competition Workshop #1: ICDC Overview & Event 
LOCATION:JC Room C, Fairfax, Virginia, United States
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2294409
DESCRIPTION:Purpose: Teach members what DECA competition is and guide them toward selecting an appropriate event.\nWorkshop Focus:\nWhat Collegiate DECA competition actually is\nCase study events vs prepared events vs written events\nHow competition works at ICDC\nPreparation time\nPresentation format\nJudge interaction\nWhat judges evaluate (rubrics, professionalism, analysis, feasibility)\nOverview of all Collegiate DECA event categories\nExamples of real DECA case prompts and winning strategies\nActivities:\nGuided walk-through of a sample case study (untimed)\nBreakdown of a scoring rubric\nEvent category interest discussion\nQ&A session addressing competition myths and concerns\nDeliverables:\nEvent interest form distributed\nCompetition handbook shared\nCompetition timeline explained\nOutcomes:\nMembers understand competition structure\nMembers feel confident exploring competition\nMembers begin narrowing down event preferences\n\nDress Code: Casual (jeans ok)\n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2294409
END:VEVENT
