UID:c4bd14d644a3ed276b41aa9e909783cb1242026_8:21:13_PM@campusgroups.com
SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:AI Speaker Series: Creating Adaptive and Personalized XR Learning Experiences with Generative AI Middleware
LOCATION:Innovation Hall Room 129, Fairfax, Virginia, United States
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2294280
DESCRIPTION:From location-based AR storytelling to personalized VR training, the Design Computing and Extended Reality (DCXR) Lab at George Mason University has developed a wide range of XR educational applications across diverse domains, including fire evacuation, construction safety, driving, fitness, rehabilitation, and nurse training. The key to creating such adaptive and personalized XR learning experiences lies in reframing XR instructional design as a generative AI problem—one that can be efficiently solved through our generative AI middleware integrated with the Unity game engine. In this talk, Craig Yu will showcase the power of this approach through a series of practical VR and AR demonstrations.\n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2294280
END:VEVENT
