UID:5dd2d353da5810289766cdd5105016721222026_10:41:36_AM@campusgroups.com
SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:Virtual Info Session - GEO Summer Study Abroad in New Zealand: Global Policy and Conservation of Marine Mammals
LOCATION:Online Event
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2293759
DESCRIPTION:Learn how to earn 6 credits over summer break and supercharge your degree in biology, environmental policy, or any other related degree with in-depth field experience studying marine mammals up close in New Zealand.\n\nhttps://masonabroad.gmu.edu/index.cfm?FuseAction=Programs.ViewProgramAngular&id=10677\n\nLed by professor of environmental policy, filmmaker, and Tropical Dolphin Research Foundation Director Dr. Jennifer Lewis, you'll:\n\n•	Learn about current conservation and policy impacting marine mammals globally (with additional focus on local issues to New Zealand)\n•	Learn about laws, stakeholders and all actions made (to date) to protect each species listed as endangered on the IUCN red list\n•	Gain practical experience in problem solving by debating the current situation for each species covered and developing ideas for new methods of action \n•	Learn from global experts (past guests have included the Secretary General of the International Whaling Commission, past chairs of the Marine Mammal Commission USA, environmental journalists, researchers, heads of environmental agencies and legal teams) \n•	Gain experience in field methods that are useful for conservation\n•	Learn from local experts to enable better well rounded understanding of the issues.\n\nDon't miss out on this amazing opportunity to earn 6 credits over 30 days experiencing first-hand New Zealand's rich marine fauna and learning how to defend it. Join us on February 5, 12, or 19 from 7 PM EST via Zoom to ask questions, seek clarification, or just learn a little about this exciting opportunity. The Information session is open to everyone.\n\nHope to see you there!\n\nMeeting Link: https://gmu.zoom.us/j/94744549530\nDress Code: Casual (jeans ok)\n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2293759
END:VEVENT
