UID:ca9fd41c0a4f060ae464b2033f01cc6d12152025_11:03:36_AM@campusgroups.com
SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:SOLD OUT - Homecoming 2026 Comedy Headliner JOSH JOHNSON
LOCATION: Sign in to download the location
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2291924
DESCRIPTION:THIS SHOW IS SOLD OUT! \n\nHomecoming Comedy Headliner Josh Joshnson\nDoors Open at 8:15 pm\nShowtime 9:00 pm\nThursday, February 5, 2026\nGeorge Mason University Center for the Arts\n\nStudent tickets are on sale NOW! 🎟️ 🎤 Josh Johnson is headlining Homecoming 2026! George Mason University Student Involvement is excited to bring you Homecoming Comedy Headliner, Josh Johnson. \n\nThe laughs begin Thursday, February 5, 2026 at 9:00 pm. Ticket information and details are available on homecoming.gmu.edu/headliner or you can use the link included in this post!  Tickets can be purchased online or in person at the Center for the Arts Ticket office or Student Involvement in Hub 2300.  Purchase in person and save! \n\nThis show is intended for an audience aged 18+.\n\nFor Student pricing, use the code "GMUJOSH26" and your GMU email address to access! \n\nWith over 7 million followers across his social media, Josh Johnson was recently called “the funniest guy on the internet” by WIRED and is a star on the rise. He is an Emmy-nominated writer, stand-up comedian, actor, and NAACP award-winner from Louisiana by way of Chicago. Johnson is currently a rotating host and correspondent on Comedy Central’s Emmy & Peabody Award-winning program The Daily Show where he was previously a writer for seven years. Johnson is also a former writer and performer on NBC’s The Tonight Show Starring Jimmy Fallon, where he made his late-night debut in 2017. \nAs a stand-up, Johnson headlines theaters, clubs, colleges, and festivals around the world and you can currently find him on his FLOWERS TOUR. He is also a prolific writer and performer who puts out weekly stand up sets on his YouTube channel. In 2024, Johnson released 28 hours of stand up and he is on track to exceed that amount this year. The content on his YouTube channel has been viewed over 340 million times by people all over the world.\n\n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2291924
END:VEVENT
