UID:a1c76a0cb098679de1e9f405972d8b5a12172025_2:30:44_PM@campusgroups.com
SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:FCPS Gatehouse Site Visit
LOCATION:TBD
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2291963
DESCRIPTION:YOU MUST APPLY TO THIS EVENT ON HANDSHAKE TO BE CONSIDERED.\n\nAs part of Education Careers Week (February 2-6), Fairfax County Public Schools (FCPS) is hosting a site visit for a group of George Mason students at their Gatehouse Administration Center on Friday, February 6, 2026. This visit will focus on the support, resources, and professional development opportunities available for future educators within one of the largest and most diverse school districts in the nation.\n\nDuring this visit, students will hear from FCPS Human Resources professionals, gain insight into the application and hiring process, and learn about programs such as Great Beginnings and other pathways designed to help new teachers thrive. You’ll also have the chance to connect with HR leadership and Mason alumni who have transitioned from the classroom into school and central office roles. Want to learn more about their careers? Visit their website: https://www.fcps.edu/careers \n\nThis is a valuable opportunity for students interested in education, teaching, or K–12 career pathways to ask questions, explore career options, and learn directly from FCPS staff.\n\nSpace is limited to 20 attendees, so apply today! The application deadline is Thursday, January 29th at 5pm!\n\nWe will contact you via email to confirm your participation and to share the next steps and site visit details such as parking, meeting location, and agenda. PLEASE NOTE: Transportation may be provided if a need is expressed.\n\nIf you have any questions, contact Ana Lobaton at alobato@gmu.edu. \n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2291963
END:VEVENT
