UID:09d951f220ea77011ef8052929cab0181262026_1:08:35_PM@campusgroups.com
SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:ICN: Saffer Guest Speaker Event
LOCATION:Johnson Center 325 Meeting Room A, Fairfax, Virginia, United States
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2294341
DESCRIPTION:     ICN is thrilled to welcome back CLS Professor Kurt Saffer for a discussion on how different branches of the military and other government and private components collaborate and navigate the information sharing environment together. Hear his advice on how you can prepare to enter a career focused on service to the United States. He will also touch on his experience working alongside the National Counterterrorism Center and the Office of the Director of National Intelligence.\n\n     Professor Saffer has a wide range of experiences through a number of leadership and analytic positions in the Air Force, particularly within the Intelligence, Surveillance, & Reconnaissance Division. He has served as the Deputy Director of NORAD & USNORTHCOM, and currently—in addition to teaching at Mason—Saffer serves as the Senior Command & Control Intelligence, Surveillance, & Reconnaissance Advisor for Spectrum Communications, Inc.\n\nMeeting Link: https://gmu.zoom.us/j/97603947165\n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2294341
END:VEVENT
