UID:4021fab78c9b9039b830b68f3006cf89172026_12:38:20_PM@campusgroups.com
SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:Career Pivot featuring Maximus
LOCATION:Online Event
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2292151
DESCRIPTION:Join us for Career Pivot Strategies: How to Redirect Your Path & Thrive featuring Flore Dorcely-Mohr, Senior Manager of Campus & Early Career Recruiting at Maximus - a Costello College of Business Corporate Partner!\n\nSpecifically for Costello College of Business students, this workshop will help those who are facing an unexpected career change and feeling uncertain about the next steps and is designed to help you confidently navigate your career transition and embrace new opportunities.\n\nIn this session, you'll learn practical strategies to:\n-Identify and leverage transferable skills: Discover how the skills you've gained in previous roles or studies can be applied to a completely new career path, making you a strong contender even in unfamiliar industries.\n-Develop effective networking strategies: Learn how to expand your professional network, build meaningful connections, and use online platforms to discover new opportunities. You’ll gain insights on how to connect with industry professionals and tap into hidden job markets.\n-Avoid burnout and stay motivated: A career pivot can be overwhelming, but with the right mindset and self-care strategies, you can stay energized and focused. We’ll explore techniques to manage stress, avoid burnout, and maintain motivation throughout your transition.\n\nBy the end of this workshop, you'll walk away with a solid action plan, new tools for managing your career pivot with confidence, and the knowledge to turn this change into an exciting opportunity for growth and success.\n\nThis virtual workshop takes place on Zoom. Pre-registration required.\n \nQuestions? Contact Costello College of Business Office of Career Services at mycareer@gmu.edu or 703-993-2140. \n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2292151
END:VEVENT
