UID:b38f209e92f3b8d049906ebc9e5faf52162026_5:11:40_PM@campusgroups.com
SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:Virtual Info Session - GEO Summer Study Abroad in Ecuador: Prosthetics in Ecuador
LOCATION:Online Event
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2292137
DESCRIPTION:Learn how you can earn 3 credits this summer applying your technical abilities to effect meaningful change in people's lives on GEO's Prosthetics in Ecuador program:\n\nhttps://masonabroad.gmu.edu/index.cfm?FuseAction=Programs.ViewProgramAngular&id=10710\n\nLed by Dr. Shani Ross, a veteran of over a decade in bioengineering and prosthetics, you'll:\n\n•	Design and fabricate prosthetics for under-served populations in Quito, Ecuador with non-profit healthcare organization Range of Motion Project (ROMP)\n•	Solve problems at the interface of engineering and life sciences\n•	Develop an understanding of effective engineering solutions to unmet clinical needs for patients by interfacing with real-world technological and environmental constraints, as well as the materials and labor available, in developing nations\n•	Demonstrate critical thinking skills in the areas of cultural analysis and intercultural understanding, with specific focus on unmet needs for prostheses in Ecuador\n•	Explore the culture of the populations you'll serve with excursions around Quito, trips to the Equator, a chocolate factory visit, and more\n\nDon't miss out on this amazing opportunity to earn academic credit while serving patients first-hand in a challenging and fulfilling environment. Join us on February 10 at 4:30 or February 11 at 4:00 PM via Zoom to ask questions, seek clarification, or just learn a little about this exciting opportunity. \n\nThese Information sessions are open to everyone.\n\nHope to see you there!\n\nMeeting Link: https://gmu.zoom.us/j/91710749450?pwd=mhkDY5lzLEk6z2AMgYVzak71H0bpgo.1\nDress Code: Casual (jeans ok)\n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2292137
END:VEVENT
