UID:3a90cd94762a5ac3b4abf1218685a482292026_9:16:54_AM@campusgroups.com
SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:Virtual Info Session -  Mason in Rome: Italian Language, Literature, and Culture, Summer 2026
LOCATION:Online Event
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2295467
DESCRIPTION:Join GEO and Dr. González Chávez to learn more about the summer Mason-led program Mason in Rome for summer 2026! \n\nMason in Rome: Italian Language, Literature & Culture, Summer 2026 (June 1 – June 27). Led by Prof. González Chávez, this summer study abroad program will take place in Rome, the Eternal City. The program aims to promote the study of Italian culture from language and literature to art and architecture, food, history, and more. Students will spend four weeks in one of the most beautiful cities in the world and study at the Centro Linguistico Italiano Dante Alighieri (CLI Dante), a boutique Italian language and culture school in Rome. Program activities will include visits to such major monuments and museums as the Capitoline Museums, the Vatican Museums and Sistine Chapel, and the Borghese Gallery. Students will also have the opportunity to visit more than more than 20 museums and archeological sites on their own using their MIC card provided by the program. In addition to a welcome dinner and a cooking class with celebrity chef Rita Monastero, students will also be welcome to participate in excursions and cultural activities offered by the school as well as to explore the city’s extraordinary and immense cultural patrimony independently. \n\nWhen in Rome, students will take two courses: (1) a course on Dante’s Inferno (Mason Core Literature), taught by Prof. González Chávez, and an Italian language course – at any level (beginner, intermediate, and advanced) – taught by highly qualified and experienced teachers at our host institution. \n\nDuring their free time students may travel independently to other world heritage sites in the Lazio region (Ostia Antica in Ostia, Villa d’Este and Hadrian’s Villa in Tivoli) or, via high-speed train, to other major Italian cities such as Florence (~1 hr. 30 mins.) and Naples (~1 hr. 15 mins.). For train schedules and other information, visit the websites for Trenitalia, the main train operator in Italy, and Italo, a private high-speed train company.  \n\nProgram highlights: \nEarn 6 credits in 4 weeks towards Mason Core and foreign language requirements. \nSpend 4 weeks in Rome, one of the most iconic cities in the world, and study Italian language, literature, and culture. \nParticipate in an array of cultural activities including a cooking class and visits to the city’s incomparable monuments and museums.\nTake advantage of free time for independent travel in the Lazio region and to other major cities like Florence and Naples. \n\nMeeting Link: https://gmu.zoom.us/j/3633482691\n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2295467
END:VEVENT
