UID:b170ed0abdae0d785af92e4e2ab196c8292026_5:14:56_PM@campusgroups.com
SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:Virtual Info Session - CRDC Summer Study Abroad: Sustainable Development, Peacebuilding, & Social Change in Morocco
LOCATION:Online Event
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2295508
DESCRIPTION:Learn how you can earn 6 credits this summer immersed in Morocco's diverse and vibrant society applying your skills and knowledge in sustainable development, peacebuilding, and social change:\n\nhttps://masonabroad.gmu.edu/index.cfm?FuseAction=Programs.ViewProgramAngular&id=10797\n\nLed by Dr. Adina Friedman, a scholar and practitioner with over 20 years of experience in peacebuilding studies in North Africa and the Middle East, you'll:\n\n•	Explore Morocco's beautiful and majestic landscapes with stops throughout Morocco\n•	Visit diverse communities (Jewish and Muslim; Arab and Amazigh/Berber; rural and urban)\n•	Learn about its history, politics, and social dynamics and will gain a deeper understanding of the ways in which the country’s diverse communities and traditions have managed to survive alongside and in relation with one another for generations\n\nDon't miss out on this amazing opportunity to earn academic credit fully immersed in a North African melting pot understanding how this diverse community faces sustainable development head-on, addresses a changing society, and navigates these challenges in a cooperative and productive way.\n\nThese Information sessions are open to everyone.\n\nHope to see you there!\n\nMeeting Link: https://nam11.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fgmu.zoom.us%2Fmeeting%2Fregister%2FqwPf93GCS0SN-db_xTYxjg&data=05%7C02%7Caciero%40gmu.edu%7C2ad4a5274e314d57255d08de684162cf%7C9e857255df574c47a0c00546460380cb%7C0%7C0%7C639062827201678412%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJFbXB0eU1hcGkiOnRydWUsIlYiOiIwLjAuMDAwMCIsIlAiOiJXaW4zMiIsIkFOIjoiTWFpbCIsIldUIjoyfQ%3D%3D%7C0%7C%7C%7C&sdata=bIgSSwwFhVVUbrLMdAf4PALMS8JBlv6m%2FQ18d%2F85f4E%3D&reserved=0\nDress Code: Casual (jeans ok)\n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2295508
END:VEVENT
