UID:db26b7f91fc5150c547d8c23353a2329172026_1:21:14_PM@campusgroups.com
SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:Career Fair Prep Workshop
LOCATION: Sign in to download the location
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2292158
DESCRIPTION:This workshop, tailored for Costello College of Business students, is designed to help you make the most out of your career fair experience! This workshop will equip you with essential strategies and tips to stand out and impress potential employers. Don't miss this opportunity to prepare yourself thoroughly and increase your chances of landing your dream job!\n\nKey Topics Include:\n-Resume and Cover Letter Tips: Crafting a polished resume and cover letter tailored for career fairs\n-Elevator Pitch: Developing and refining a concise, impactful introduction\n-Researching Employers: Identifying target companies and understanding their needs\n-Dressing for Success: Choosing the right professional attire to make a great first impression\n-Effective Communication: Engaging with recruiters confidently and professionally\n-Follow-Up Strategies: Learning how to follow up effectively after the fair\n\nThis workshop takes place in-person in Enterprise Hall 038. Pre-registration required.\n \nQuestions? Contact Costello College of Business Office of Career Services at mycareer@gmu.edu or 703-993-2140. \n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2292158
END:VEVENT
