UID:2123898462fbe70dc37abc744aeb53811222026_1:34:38_PM@campusgroups.com
SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE: Korean Language and Culture - Summer 2026 Study Abroad
LOCATION:Online Event
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2293874
DESCRIPTION:Come learn about this amazing study abroad opportunity in South Korea. This 4.5-week summer program offers a fully immersive experience, including Korean language classes, culture and history lessons, and cultural activities like traditional crafts, dance, and calligraphy. Participants spend the first 2.5 weeks at the Mason Korea campus in the urban environmental of Incheon Songdo, followed by 2 weeks in the beautiful and unique natural environment of Jeju Island. The program includes field trips to Seoul, Incheon, Songdo, and the DMZ (the border between the North and South Korea). This program is open to beginner Korean language students; you do not need any Korean proficiency to participate! \n\nMeeting Link: https://gmu.zoom.us/j/4471370677\nDress Code: Casual (jeans ok)\n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2293874
END:VEVENT
