UID:d2ba1b680c447b89d848fbbdc91476c6252026_12:31:24_PM@campusgroups.com
SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:Virtual Info Session -  Greece - ONE Health Education Summer 2026                 
LOCATION:Online Event
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2295170
DESCRIPTION:Join GEO to learn more about the Greece - ONE Health Education program for summer 2026.  \nOne Health Education offers a comprehensive look at health through an interdisciplinary lens, connecting human health, animal health, and environmental factors. This study abroad course integrates education, culture, psychology, public health policy, economics, and ethics to provide a holistic understanding of health challenges. Students will collaborate across various fields and cultures, working together to solve complex global health issues in real-world settings. The course emphasizes critical thinking and problem-solving, bringing together diverse perspectives to address pressing One Health challenges.\n\n\nProgram Highlights \nStudents from various fields, including education, social sciences, health sciences, and other interdisciplinary areas, can take One Health Education. It is cross-listed and students can register for  EDEP 497/597, PSYCH 461, and GCH 491.\n\nStudents will have the opportunity to think critically and solve complex global health challenges through collaboration across various fields.\n\nMeeting Link: https://gmu.zoom.us/j/3633482691\n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2295170
END:VEVENT
