UID:f64d084a172a0f68a0b423f5bf74eb7f1232026_10:55:29_AM@campusgroups.com
SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:Black Queer Liberation House Ball Challenge
LOCATION: Sign in to download the location
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2293985
DESCRIPTION:Join the LGBTQ+ Resources Center, Center for Leadership and Intercultural Engagement (CLIE), and African and African American Studies (AAAS) for an educational and entertaining Ballroom Challenge Event to celebrate Black History Month!\n\nAt the Black Queer Liberation House Ball Challenge Event, students will form their own houses, mirroring those commonly formed in ballroom culture. Together, each house will face off to answer trivia questions and show their moves on the red carpet to be rated by judges and recieve points for their team. Trivia questions will surround pivotal and iconic figures and events in Black and Queer history, so know your stuff!\nDress Code: Casual (jeans ok)\n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2293985
END:VEVENT
