UID:56196f8162cc88ec8e0722759944e5e3292026_5:58:38_PM@campusgroups.com
SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:Virtual Info Session - CRDC Summer Virtual Field Work with Syrians in Conflict, Recovery, and Peacebuilding, Summer 2026
LOCATION:Online Event
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2295512
DESCRIPTION:Learn about CRDC's groundbreaking online summer study abroad course, led by Dr. Marc Gopin. In this course, you'll engage directly with Syrian survivors, refugees, activists, and conflict healers in the process of rebuilding Syrian society.\n\nhttps://masonabroad.gmu.edu/index.cfm?FuseAction=Programs.ViewProgramAngular&id=10777\n\nLed by Dr. Marc Gopin, a peacebuilding and conflict healing professional with decades of academic and hands-on experience, you'll study, observe, or practice:\n\n● Conflict Healing\n\n● Compassionate Reasoning\n\n● Social Network Practice (See To Make the Earth Whole readings)\n\n● Nonviolent conflict management and mitigation in divided conflict situations (managing the conflict and moving it in a nonviolent direction)\n\n● Skills of citizen diplomacy\n\n● The art of working across sectarian lines\n\n● Human rights promotion and successful conflict resolution\n\n● Civil society building\n\n● Women's empowerment that leads to more resilience and peace\n\n● Children's needs as a shared love across many lines that leads to less violence\n\n● The role of youth\n\n● Trauma and mental health care, leading to more rational thinking and problem-solving\n\n● Solidarity creation across many lines – sectarian lines, gender lines – through acts of compassion and generosity\n\n● Future Planning and Prospection Science for possible futures\n\nExplorations will be made of goal-oriented and principled processes of coalition building that focus less on what or who is being opposed and more on the ethical practices of what can be built for the future, as well as an ethical approach to nonviolent social change that is radically inclusive in the process of building peaceful post-conflict societies.\n\nThe course will feature daily lectures by Dr. Marc Gopin, as well as engagement with Syrian survivors, refugees, activists, and peacemakers.\n\nDon't miss out on this amazing opportunity to earn academic credit over the summer exploring and practice innovative peacebuilding techniques as Syria strives towards a brighter future.\n\nThese Information sessions are open to everyone.\n\nHope to see you there!\n\nMeeting Link: https://gmu.zoom.us/meeting/register/gBNxLDJwQZqJnA3Z_ffCDw\nDress Code: Casual (jeans ok)\n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2295512
END:VEVENT
