UID:41e4f116a6e828ab89202187578714f61302026_6:22:17_PM@campusgroups.com
SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:Informational Event: Discover the Oldest Latino Fraternity in Existence
LOCATION:Johnson Center 3rd Floor Room D, Fairfax, Virginia, United States
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2294699
DESCRIPTION:Discover the legacy of the oldest Latino fraternity in existence. Phi Iota Alpha Fraternity, Inc., founded on December 26, 1931, carries a historic lineage that traces back to the first Latin American student organization established in 1898. Rooted in leadership, culture, and academic excellence, the fraternity continues to uphold a tradition of empowering Latino students across generations.\nDress Code: Casual (jeans ok)\n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2294699
END:VEVENT
