UID:36efbc36973c001aefd639ddbecc2618192026_12:09:40_PM@campusgroups.com
SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:RESEARCH, PRESENT, & MOTIVATE THE FUTURE: Undergraduate Abstract and Poster Submissions
LOCATION:HUB Ballroom, Fairfax Campus , Fairfax, Virginia, United States
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2292256
DESCRIPTION:Calling all undergraduate STEM students! You are invited to take part in the "Design the Future" Research Poster Competition, where you can exhibit your research, creativity, and problem-solving skills. This is your chance to present your innovative ideas to a judging panel of CEC alumni and corporate partners and compete for first, second, and third-place prizes! Whether you're exploring innovative technologies or tackling real-world issues, your work has the potential to mold tomorrow. Don’t miss this opportunity to share your insights, gain valuable feedback, and make an impact! \n\n\nNote: The cap on posters that will accepted to be displayed is twenty-five (25), though it should be noted that the office may accept less than twenty-five (25) posters. If accepted student researchers or student research teams will be invited to present their cutting-edge research to a panel of CEC alumni and industry leaders judges. \n\nPoster Presentation: Wednesday, February 18 | 5:30 pm – 7:30 pm | HUB Ballroom, Fairfax Campus \n\nPrizes will the awarded to the top three posters presented and judged by CEC's invited guests. \nDress Code: Business Casual\n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2292256
END:VEVENT
