UID:d025c226c2522ffd00ddbcfcca87a7291232026_10:51:49_AM@campusgroups.com
SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:Lunar New Year Festival (Tết Nguyên Đán)
LOCATION:JC Georges (Third Floor), United States
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2293984
DESCRIPTION:Tet Nguyen Dan is the most significant cultural festival in Vietnamese tradition, marking the arrival of spring and the beginning of the Lunar New Year. To share the meaning of Tết, we will host an event where students can learn about Vietnamese culture through traditions, food, and customs. Funding will support cultural displays (peach and apricot blossoms), traditional culinary offerings (Banh Chung/Banh Tet), and the "Li Xi" (lucky money) tradition to foster an inclusive environment and celebrate cultural heritage on campus. One of the highlights of the event will be playing Vietnamese board games, which are especially popular and highly anticipated during Tết among young people like our peers, creating a fun and interactive way to connect with the culture.\n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2293984
END:VEVENT
