UID:767ba75c47397b3477361eb000dcb32d292026_5:42:02_PM@campusgroups.com
SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:Virtual Info Session - CRDC Summer Virtual Study Abroad: Israel & Palestine Reflective Practice, Summer 2026
LOCATION:Online Event
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2295511
DESCRIPTION:Learn about CRDC's groundbreaking online summer study abroad course, led by Dr. Marc Gopin. In this course, you'll experience new approaches to conflict healing in the uniquely intractable Israel Palestine conflict by direct, firsthand encounters with change practitioners and communities across the spectrum of Israel & Palestine.\n\nhttps://masonabroad.gmu.edu/index.cfm?FuseAction=Programs.ViewProgram&Program_ID=10773\n\nLed by Dr. Marc Gopin, a peacebuilding and conflict healing professional with decades of academic and hands-on experience, you'll:\n\n•	Hear directly from from practitioners who, in various ways, have sought to reduce violence, promote peace and justice, and foster relationships across adversarial lines\n•	Engage in critical reflective practice techniques, including how to measure one's words and actions to honor and reflect on conflict and effectively practice conflict healing and peacebuilding.\n•	 Integrate new approaches to peacebuilding in a uniquely intractable conflict, where CRDC has innovated direct interventions in social justice practice, study, and engagement, including Conflict Healing, Compassionate Reasoning, Future Visioning, Bridge Walking, Peer Support, and Social Network Practice\n\nThe course has been carefully engineered to support agents of change, including women who are often absent or underutilized from patriarchal secular and religious power structures globally in places of conflict. In addition, the seminar and its experiences employ a fundamentally multiple-narrative approach to understanding the reality on the ground in all its complexity.\n\nThe course will feature daily lectures by Dr. Marc Gopin, as well as engagement with Israelis, Palestinians, activists, and peacemakers.\n\nDon't miss out on this amazing opportunity to earn academic credit over the summer while actively engaging first-hand with regional changemakers.\n\nThese Information sessions are open to everyone.\n\nHope to see you there!\n\nMeeting Link: https://nam11.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fgmu.zoom.us%2Fmeeting%2Fregister%2FGqpIGZe3RjKV1dAKWg8ouQ&data=05%7C02%7Caciero%40gmu.edu%7C2ad4a5274e314d57255d08de684162cf%7C9e857255df574c47a0c00546460380cb%7C0%7C0%7C639062827201700452%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJFbXB0eU1hcGkiOnRydWUsIlYiOiIwLjAuMDAwMCIsIlAiOiJXaW4zMiIsIkFOIjoiTWFpbCIsIldUIjoyfQ%3D%3D%7C0%7C%7C%7C&sdata=0lgH5iVF%2Fp8WGe9NivNR4RSjI27xVGazVtT05rBIQ%2B4%3D&reserved=0\nDress Code: Casual (jeans ok)\n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2295511
END:VEVENT
