UID:d140e782ee1ddac479076d978924da622202026_9:28:40_AM@campusgroups.com
SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:Fund for the Public Interest Information Sessions
LOCATION:Student Union Building, Career Services Office, Room 3438, Fairfax Campus, 4400 University Drive, Fairfax, VA 22030, United States
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2296175
DESCRIPTION:Make a difference for pollinators, old growth forests, and fight plastic pollution this summer!  Join Fund for the Public Interest to learn about working on a campaign that engages citizens directly. Their canvassers talk to people one-on-one and make thousands of peoples voices heard through petitions, donations, emails, and meetings. Together, you can make a real impact on our environment, our democracy, and beyond. \n\nStudents will meet in large conference room area for a group overview about the Fund for the Public Interest and the available jobs, before being taken into individual interviews. These information sessions will take place at 10:00am, 1:30pm, and 3:30pm. No pre-registration required.\nDress Code: Business Casual\n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2296175
END:VEVENT
