UID:e88fccc54ff87ad08309ac44fe945f8612172025_2:08:28_PM@campusgroups.com
SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:Ski Trip to Timberline, WV
LOCATION:TBD
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2291945
DESCRIPTION:Join Outdoor Adventures for our annual ski trip!  This year will take us to the slopes of wild and wonderful West Virginia.  Registration includes lift ticket, equipment rentals, and transportation.  If you have your own skis/snowboard, please contact nwilso8@gmu.edu for steps to waive the equipment rental fee. \n\nDifficulty: Beginner – Advanced – Timberline has a variety of terrain to cater to all skill levels, from beginner-friendly easy slopes to expert only black diamonds.  This trip DOES NOT include lessons, though lessons cost $25/hour and information can be found here: https://timberlinemountain.com/ski-snowboard-lessons/  \n\nAmenities: Restrooms, running water, and prepared food at the lodge and base area \n\nTravel Time: Approx. 3 hours each way \n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2291945
END:VEVENT
