UID:320582659d61035cc96f19a640548833172026_1:32:03_PM@campusgroups.com
SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:Cover Letter Workshop
LOCATION:Online Event
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2292161
DESCRIPTION:Join us for a cover letter writing workshop tailored for Costello College of Business students!\nYour cover letter is more than an introduction—it’s your chance to tell your story and stand out in a competitive job market. In this interactive workshop, our career advisors will guide you through the essentials of persuasive writing, helping you create tailored, impactful cover letters that showcase your unique value.\n\nKey Takeaways:\n-Cover Letter Essentials: Understand the purpose and importance of cover letters in the application process.\n-Structure & Tone: Learn how to craft attention-grabbing openings, highlight achievements, and express enthusiasm for the role.\n-Personalization Techniques: Discover strategies to align your narrative with company culture and job requirements.\n-Showcase Your Value: Articulate your strengths and demonstrate how you can contribute to the employer’s success.\n-Polish & Perfect: Master proofreading and refinement techniques to ensure clarity and professionalism.\n\nThis virtual workshop takes place on Zoom. Pre-registration required.\n \nQuestions? Contact Costello College of Business Office of Career Services at mycareer@gmu.edu or 703-993-2140. \n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2292161
END:VEVENT
