DESCRIPTION:Join FBI Special Agent Geoff Rayes to learn about the paid Honors Internship Program – Summer 2027 and other career opportunities with the FBI. This session will take place on Monday, February 23 from 1:00 - 2:00pm ET.  Agent Rayes will share an overview of employment with the FBI, tips for success, and be available for Q&A.  Be a part of a team that ensures we stay ahead of new advances in technology, terrorism, and intelligence threats.  United States citizenship is required.\n\nThe Honors Internship Program application cycle will begin February 9, 2026. Students must apply by March 5, 2026, to be considered for the summer internship period of June – August 2027. For more information about the Honors Internship Program, please visit:  https://fbijobs.gov/students-and-graduates#honors-internship-program\n\nDress Code: Business Casual\n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2296072
END:VEVENT
