UID:39c5c7fccd87e0add78a0a3115bd0e61172026_1:37:38_PM@campusgroups.com
SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:Resume 101: Basics & Formatting Workshop featuring Aston Carter
LOCATION: Sign in to download the location
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2292163
DESCRIPTION:Join us for a resume writing workshop featuring Peter Tu, Practice Lead & Business Development Manager at Aston Carter. \n\nIn this hands-on session, designed specifically for Costello College of Business students, our expert career advisors will guide you through the foundational elements of creating a polished, professional resume. You’ll learn how to structure your resume for maximum impact, choose the right format for your career goals, and ensure your document is visually appealing and easy to read.\n\nKey Takeaways:\n-Understand the essential components of a strong resume layout.\n-Learn formatting best practices to make your resume stand out.\n-Discover how to organize sections for clarity and professionalism.\n\nThis workshop takes place in-person in Enterprise Hall 038. Pre-registration required.\n \nQuestions? Contact Costello College of Business Office of Career Services at mycareer@gmu.edu or 703-993-2140. \n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2292163
END:VEVENT
