UID:bb3c4dad53e30abd613582df9a385836172026_1:35:02_PM@campusgroups.com
SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:Interviewing in the U.S. Workshop: Insights from an Alumni
LOCATION:Online Event
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2292162
DESCRIPTION:Join us for a job search workshop featuring alumni, Benjamin Huy Mai! \n\nNavigating the U.S. job market as an international student comes with its own unique challenges—especially when it comes to interviews. This workshop, tailored for Costello College of Business students, is designed to help you feel more confident and prepared as you take on job or internship interviews in an American workplace setting. \n\nOur career advising team will offer helpful tips and practical guidance to support your success in U.S.-based interviews. Whether you’re just getting started or actively applying, this workshop is a valuable opportunity to learn what to expect and how to position yourself as a strong candidate. \n\nDon’t miss out on this chance to gain an edge in your job search and boost your confidence before your next big interview. \n\nThis virtual workshop takes place on Zoom. Pre-registration required.\n \nQuestions? Contact Costello College of Business Office of Career Services at mycareer@gmu.edu or 703-993-2140. \n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2292162
END:VEVENT
