UID:72675d309ce17f5088154c830fc3b0b21142026_4:44:25_PM@campusgroups.com
SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:International Cafe: Africa Edition
LOCATION:Johnson Center Bistro, Fairfax, Virginia, United States
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2293095
DESCRIPTION:The Office of International Programs and Services (OIPS) and the Center for Leadership and Intercultural Engagement (CLIE) invite you to our upcoming International Café: African Edition on Wednesday, February 25, 2026, from 1:00 p.m. to 3:00 p.m. at the Johnson Center Bistro.\n\nOur first International Café of the semester will highlight the cultures and students of Eritrea, Ethiopia, Ghana, Kenya, Nigeria, and South Africa! We are excited to collaborate with the African Student Association, Eritrean-Ethiopian Student Association, and Nigerian Students Association for this event.\n\nCome learn about these vibrant countries, celebrate their rich cultures, and enjoy free snacks and drinks! Join us as we continue celebrating Black & African Heritage Month!\n\nFREE T-SHIRTS WILL BE GIVEN OUT WHILE SUPPLIES LAST! \nDress Code: Casual (jeans ok)\n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2293095
END:VEVENT
