SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:Interview Skills Workshop featuring Deloitte
LOCATION:Online Event
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2292164
DESCRIPTION:Join us for an interviewing workshop featuring Megan Farina, Specialist Leader, Cyber and Strategic Risk at Deloitte.\n\nIn this workshop, designed specifically for Costello College of Business students, you'll learn to elevate your confidence, polish your presentation, and navigate the interview process with finesse. In this interactive workshop, our career advisors will provide expert guidance and practical strategies to help you stand out and succeed in any interview setting.\n\nKey Takeaways:\n-Preparing for Success: Learn effective preparation techniques, including research strategies, anticipating common questions, and crafting impactful responses.\n-Presenting Your Best Self: Discover the art of confident communication and professional etiquette to project authenticity and poise.\n-Excelling in Different Formats: Understand the nuances of behavioral, case, and panel interviews—and gain strategies to shine in each.\n-Handling Challenging Questions: Master techniques for responding to tough questions with clarity and confidence.\n-Post-Interview Follow-Up: Explore best practices for thank-you notes and follow-up communications to leave a lasting impression.\n\nThis virtual workshop takes place on Zoom. Pre-registration required.\n \nQuestions? Contact Costello College of Business Office of Career Services at mycareer@gmu.edu or 703-993-2140. \n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2292164
END:VEVENT
