UID:585bf39c82319177bf1fc39beff6e3072112026_10:56:58_AM@campusgroups.com
SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:Platypus Film Screening 
LOCATION:Innovation 319, Fairfax, Virginia, United States
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2295630
DESCRIPTION:1863: Following the Union victory at Antietam, Lincoln's Emancipation Proclamation recasts the Civil War as a second American Revolution: a struggle to fulfill the promises of 1776 by abolishing slavery and extending free labor. The persistence of anti-black racism in the US after Reconstruction seemed to belie the struggle for social equality and freedom exemplified by Abolitionism, but this history continues to demand redemption.\n\nPlatypus asks: What does the American Civil War mean for the Left?\n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2295630
END:VEVENT
