UID:566b84952aed358d84b76b4eadd70d871262026_5:49:49_PM@campusgroups.com
SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:Honors College Challenge Day 
LOCATION:Fenwick Main Reading Room, University Library, Fairfax Campus, Fairfax, Virginia, United States
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2294362
DESCRIPTION:Join us for Honors College Challenge Day, a half-day friendly competition to build your network and your resume while creatively addressing a real-world problem posed by our partners.\n\nPartners will include: \n- Food For Others, which works to reduce food insecurity \n- MVLE, which provides employment and support services to people with disabilities\n- Britepaths, which works to address food insecurity by providing food, financial assistance, financial education, and wokforce development services.\n- ScholarCHIPS, which provides mentoring and financial support to college students with incarcerated parents\n- The Arc of Greater Prince William, which provides opportunities for persons with developmental disabilities to achieve their potential\n- Hope For The Warriors, which provides services to support veterans and their families.\n\nEnjoy free lunch while sharpening your professional skills and connecting with local leaders, George Mason alums, and fellow students. All participants will have the chance to mingle and work in teams with plenty of support from peer mentors. \n\nTake advantage of this opportunity to make a difference while developing skills and having experiences that matter! \n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2294362
END:VEVENT
