UID:631295458c7c60d8df1fea9288e0f2a31222026_12:04:25_PM@campusgroups.com
SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:MIX Hacks: w/ James Hope
LOCATION:Horizon Hall 1408, Fairfax, Virginia, United States
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2293823
DESCRIPTION:James Hope, a senior makerspace associate uses this loose workshop framework to demonstrate various methods, techniques and processes necessary to successfully build an open source Voron 3D printer which integrates 3D printed parts, wiring, and assembly in the build of the printer. The entire event runs from 1-3pm, during a staff shift, but attendees can come for increments of time. Future "MIX Hacks" workshops may expose the detailed inner-working process of staff working on their personal or MIX directed projects that may be universally relevant to the Mason community. \n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2293823
END:VEVENT
