UID:ca64467c33ae5a6ab08b2c46bf021a391122026_6:13:20_PM@campusgroups.com
SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:Unpacking Conflict: Movies
LOCATION:Johnson Center Meeting Room C, Fairfax, Virginia, United States
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2292444
DESCRIPTION:Conflict on the Big Screen\nFilms spark conversations and have themes that go way beyond the screen. Join our next panel as they unpack the real conflicts shaping today’s movie landscape—representation, ethics, creative control, audience backlash, and the power stories have to influence culture. This session invites students into the questions people actually want answered: What responsibilities do storytellers have, and what happens when art and impact collide? Pack a lunch or grab one from the eateries in the JC, and join us for this discussion.\nDress Code: Casual (jeans ok)\n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2292444
END:VEVENT
