UID:4b9fbefb1d2dc923b71d37a73fbe83191222026_8:32:20_AM@campusgroups.com
SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:Virtual Info Session - GEO Summer Study Abroad in The Balkans: Reconciliation and Post-Conflict Reconstruction in the Aftermath of Mass Violence
LOCATION:Online Event
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2293751
DESCRIPTION:Learn how to earn 3-6 credits over summer break and supercharge your degree in conflict analysis & resolution, government, or any other related degree with in-depth field experience on The Balkans Case: Reconciliation and Post-Conflict Reconstruction in the Aftermath of Mass Violence:\n\nhttps://masonabroad.gmu.edu/index.cfm?FuseAction=Programs.ViewProgramAngular&id=10419\n\nLed by Dr. Borislava Manojlovic, a veteran of over 20 years in regional security, genocide prevention, and related topics, you'll:\n\n•	Explore historic cities and landmarks\n•	Enjoy local experiences and excursions\n•	Engage with experts in the region\n•	Build lifelong friendships with fellow students from both Mason Korea and Mason Fairfax campuses\n\nDon't miss out on this amazing opportunity to earn academic credit while discovering the beauty of one of Europe’s most fascinating regions. Join us on December 17 from 7-8 PM EST (December 18 from 9-10 AM Korean time) via Zoom to ask questions, seek clarification, or just learn a little about this exciting opportunity. The Information session is open to everyone.\n\nHope to see you there!\n\nMeeting Link: https://gmu.zoom.us/j/93172584992?pwd=91GNeQc3JaVCa1blbNtd7JdcbY9GtB.1\nDress Code: Casual (jeans ok)\n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2293751
END:VEVENT
