UID:6c8d55db9919467fd3b3aff8337636e6162026_2:13:41_PM@campusgroups.com
SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:Spring into Well-Being: Brewing Connections (SciTech)
LOCATION:Katherine G. Johnson Hall- Atrium, Fairfax, Virginia, United States
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2292107
DESCRIPTION:Join us for a cozy drink and meaningful conversations that spark connection.\n\nStop by our Brewing Connections pop-ups at SciTech, Arlington, and Fairfax campuses—a warm and welcoming space to spark connection and support your well-being. Enjoy a cozy beverage and a meaningful conversation hosted by the Center for the Advancement of Well-Being and Mason Chooses Kindness. Kindness Ambassadors and Student Strengths Coaches will be on hand to engage in guided chats using conversation cards that explore a variety of topics, including strengths, and well-being strategies, and kindness in action.\n\nDress Code: Casual (jeans ok)\n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2292107
END:VEVENT
