UID:515407c03a13e84028df0d5db429d57a222026_5:13:01_PM@campusgroups.com
SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:A Conversation with the Authors: Recent Books Published about Migration & Displacement
LOCATION:1204 Merten Hall , 4441 George Mason Blvd University Hall, Fairfax 22030, United States
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2294955
DESCRIPTION:Join us for a timely conversation with Mason authors whose recent books examine migration and displacement across global, historical, and lived contexts. Through an engaging panel discussion, the authors will reflect on the motivations behind their books, key findings from their research, and the broader social, political, and human implications of migration today. Topics will include displacement and belonging, state policies and borders, gender and family dynamics, and the everyday experiences of migrant and displaced communities.\n \nFollowing the moderated discussion, there will be time for audience questions and dialogue.\n \nThe event is free and open to students, faculty, researchers, practitioners, and community members.\n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2294955
END:VEVENT
