UID:e5d1b5fbe1b876aa052b70ff0deede121202026_11:05:12_PM@campusgroups.com
SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:Mason Lobbies 2026
LOCATION:On-Campus, Richmond, Fairfax, Virginia, United States
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2293624
DESCRIPTION:Mason Lobbies 2026 continues our tradition of students travelling to Richmond to advocate for students' needs to our legislators in the Virginia General Assembly. On March 5th, we'll be leaving the GMU Fairfax Campus early (~6:00 AM), arriving in Richmond and meeting with legislators, then returning by ~3:30 PM. Transportation and food will be provided at no cost to attendees - plus a free green-and-gold scarf! \n\nMason Lobbies 2026 is your chance to stand up for issues that you care about, build your network with Virginia's decision-makers, and add advocacy experience to your résumé. This is for all students and all majors, because we're all affected by Mason's funding and state policies, and all of us have a voice. Please email sg@gmu.edu and gcrouch3@gmu.edu with any questions!\n\nhttps://sg.gmu.edu/join/mason-lobbies/\nDress Code: Business Formal\n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2293624
END:VEVENT
