UID:d4f87f2311083cd4832e3858184d643b2112026_3:37:09_PM@campusgroups.com
SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:American Woodcock Walk
LOCATION:Sully Woodlands Park, 5320 Pleasant Valley Rd, Centreville 20120, United States
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2295669
DESCRIPTION:Join the Wildlife Society at Sully Woodlands on March 7th for a Woodcock walk! For a short time every year American Woodcocks perform their spectacular display flights on spring evenings, giving us a chance to see these amazing birds at their best. \n\nParking is available outside the entrance, a gravel road on the west side of Pleasant Valley Road as well as on the side on Pleasant Valley Road. \n\nThis event will involve a small amount of hiking to reach the Woodcock watch area  and binoculars and headlamps are recommended but not required, however they will not be provided.  \n\n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2295669
END:VEVENT
