UID:1550bd7c421c9a8a5ca169ab028588482242026_3:08:41_PM@campusgroups.com
SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:CSGSA x Pitch Labs Tech Talk: Navigating  Innovation, AI, and Entrepreneurship with Damon  Feldman
LOCATION:Fuse 1327, Fairfax, Virginia, United States
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2296306
DESCRIPTION:George Mason University’s Computer Science Graduate Student Association (CSGSA), in collaboration with Pitch Labs, is excited to host a special tech‑entrepreneurship event featuring Damon Feldman, an accomplished technologist, founder, and AI‑driven healthcare innovator.\nDamon Feldman is the President and Co‑Founder of Advocara, an AI‑based healthcare navigation startup working to bring transparency to medical billing. His career spans leadership roles in customer engineering, large‑scale data integration, and complex system design across healthcare, government, and enterprise technology. Damon holds a Ph.D. in Computer Science and has led engineering initiatives for organizations of various sizes and industries.\n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2296306
END:VEVENT
