UID:187c2d2a96598bcd7a07af8c64c37e36392026_9:24:09_PM@campusgroups.com
SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:Henna2Heal
LOCATION:Fenwick, Spiritual Center, A110, Fairfax Campus, Fairfax, Virginia, United States
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2296926
DESCRIPTION:Henna2Heal is a charity henna event celebrating Eid al-Fitr, a religious holiday observed by Muslims that marks the completion of the month of Ramadan, a period of fasting, reflection, and spiritual growth. Henna is a traditional cultural and religious practice commonly used during Eid celebrations, symbolizing joy, gratitude, and community.\nThe event is intended to create a welcoming space for students to learn about the significance of Ramadan and Eid while participating in a cultural tradition associated with the holiday. Through this event, we hope to increase awareness of Muslim traditions, encourage interfaith understanding, and provide an opportunity for students from different backgrounds to engage with and learn about Islamic cultural practices.\nIn addition, the event will serve as a charity fundraiser, with proceeds going toward humanitarian aid efforts.\n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2296926
END:VEVENT
