UID:91c9305b10cbe05a9696e63cef6bbd573122026_2:41:36_PM@campusgroups.com
SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:
LOCATION:Merten Hall room 1204 and online via Zoom, Fairfax, Virginia, United States
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2296991
DESCRIPTION:Understanding how human activities impact ecosystems and the behavioral ecology and physiology of wildlife populations is critical for successful conservation. At the same time, it is imperative to engage with people who neighbor wildlife areas to find sustainable solutions for their livelihoods. My research takes a transdisciplinary approach to understand the ecological consequences of human activities and interventions that promote biodiversity and ecosystem health. I use data-driven and community-led approaches to address issues at the human-wildlife interface and the interconnectedness of humans, other animals, and the environment. In this talk, I will discuss my research with endangered species and communities in Madagascar and Uganda, as well as other sites.\n\n\nMeeting Link: https://gmu.zoom.us/meeting/register/wMWVMivRSw67yqdHe3sxQw#/registration\n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2296991
END:VEVENT
