UID:7e8e1c65334e6be90cf1743f3b177ffb322026_9:58:52_AM@campusgroups.com
SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:FREE Rock Climbing Anchors Clinic 
LOCATION:TBD
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2296650
DESCRIPTION:Come join our FREE educational clinic session on building basic outdoor climbing anchors. This hour-long instruction will equip attendees with the foundational knowledge to construct safe, reliable top-rope anchors in an outdoor setting and give you greater confidence in your abilities for future climbing days.  <p>\n\n<p>\n\nNo prior anchor-building experience is necessary. We will cover essential concepts including anchor components, material selection, redundancy, equalization, and basic safety principles. All necessary equipment will be provided during the course of instruction, and participants will have the opportunity to practice hands-on skills under guided supervision.\n\n<p>\n\n<p>Whether you're transitioning from indoor climbing to outdoor routes or simply looking to strengthen your foundational skills, this clinic is a great place to start.\n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2296650
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
