UID:c2f7b2f688658d1c8bf56ad64f06f6221292025_1:26:15_PM@campusgroups.com
SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:Real Talk: Advocating for Workplace Accommodations
LOCATION:Online Event
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2291815
DESCRIPTION:For a person with a disability or chronic illness, advocating for accommodations can be overwhelming if you’re not sure how to ask for what you need. This workshop reviews your rights and provides practical tips for effective communication with your employer, including addressing potential challenges when requesting accommodations. Learn how to advocate for yourself and create a work environment where you can truly thrive, with insights from an expert on the Americans with Disabilities Act (ADA) and firsthand experiences from George Mason alumni. \n\nZoom to join: https://gmu.zoom.us/j/92383028047\n\nThis event will take place on Zoom. For those needing disability-related accommodations, please contact Career Services at careers@gmu.edu by March 4.\n \nThis event is open to all George Mason students and alumni.\n\nMeeting Link: https://gmu.zoom.us/j/92383028047\n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2291815
END:VEVENT
