UID:bd62eef1b40179793975a419c2b86145332026_11:42:49_AM@campusgroups.com
SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:Colombia in Focus: From Awareness to Action
LOCATION:JC Room D, Fairfax, Virginia, United States
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2296731
DESCRIPTION:Colombia in Focus: From Awareness to Action is the opening event of Phi Iota Alpha Fraternity, Inc.’s Latin American Initiative (LAI) 2026. This program is designed to provide context and understanding around this year’s country of focus, Colombia, while highlighting the social and educational challenges faced by many communities.\n\nDuring this event, attendees will learn about Colombia’s cultural significance, current educational inequalities, and the work being done by Fundación Pies Descalzos, the philanthropic organization founded by Colombian artist Shakira that focuses on improving access to quality education for vulnerable communities. Through discussion and reflection, the event will connect awareness to meaningful action and introduce the broader goals of the Latin American Initiative.\n\nThis event serves as the foundation for the LAI series, leading into Colombia en Vivo on April 2 and culminating in the Miss Latina America Pageant on April 21.\n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2296731
END:VEVENT
