UID:7d19479b31b1c74ed7f260130ae7f7c01232025_1:52:05_PM@campusgroups.com
SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:Clearance Ready: Introduction to Security Clearances
LOCATION:Johnson Center, 325, Meeting Room A, Fairfax Campus, 4400 University Drive, Fairfax, VA 22030, United States
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2291743
DESCRIPTION:Interested in working for organizations like the FBI, ManTech, the State Department, NIH, NASA, Deloitte, Booz Allen, EPA or Northrup Grumman? A security clearance is required for all jobs with U.S. federal government agencies and most partner companies. To maximize your career options in the DC metro area, join us to learn more about what a security clearance is, why it is important, and what is included in the background check to attain one. Interact with employers requiring a security clearance and learn about the dos and don'ts of the process. This event is part of the University Career Services Clearance Ready Program. \nDress Code: Business Casual\n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2291743
END:VEVENT
