UID:b6654e3f9198d78a37622d024ea3c51b3122026_3:24:16_PM@campusgroups.com
SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:
LOCATION:JC meeting room D room 333 and virtually through Zoom, Fairfax, Virginia, United States
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2296992
DESCRIPTION:Limiting global warming requires both reducing greenhouse gas emissions and increasing removal rates of atmospheric CO2, leading to dramatic transformations of Earth’s landscapes. These actions will affect Earth’s biodiversity through two major mechanisms: by helping mitigate climate change globally and by altering habitat availability locally. In this talk, I’ll combine global biodiversity databases with earth system modelling to investigate how the choices that society makes in addressing climate change will affect biodiversity. I’ll show that by failing to account for the land-use transformations associated with reaching net-zero we may inadvertently hasten biodiversity loss. Finally, I’ll explore how we can use science to inform policies that provide ‘win-win’ outcomes for biodiversity and climate.\n\n\nMeeting Link: https://gmu.zoom.us/meeting/register/JtpBwBT4S-WPSVNPXLQOvg#/registration\n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2296992
END:VEVENT
