UID:ad572dc7a93d6d532212ce47e9fa74b62262026_9:14:56_AM@campusgroups.com
SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:Real Life 101: Finding Happiness and Purpose in a Stressful, Uncertain Era
LOCATION:Van Metre Hall, First Floor Auditorium Room 134, Mason Square, George Mason University, 3351, Fairfax Dr, Arlington 22201, United States
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2296533
DESCRIPTION:What is the secret to happiness? Could it be as simple as finding one’s purpose? Or as simple as to stop trying to be happy and instead, make others happy? Join our panel as we expand upon a column by Washington Post writer Dana Milbank. We’ll explore research findings from Cornell as well as George Mason University. Learn about how others have found happiness through purpose. To enhance the event, meet and greet with some local nonprofits to find out how you might engage and find your purpose! Light refreshments provided.\n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2296533
END:VEVENT
