UID:b0501c8bbc441ee3ed7084228253af8d332026_7:23:32_PM@campusgroups.com
SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:How Local Government Works: A Discussion With Arlington County Board Members
LOCATION:Online Event
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2296762
DESCRIPTION:What does local government actually do? In recognition of Sunshine Week, this moderated panel brings together members of the Arlington County Board to discuss the structure, functions, and responsibilities of county government, with particular attention to transparency and public accountability. Moderated by Policy and Government Librarian Lorena Jordan, Arlington County Board members will discuss decision-making processes, policy development, and intergovernmental collaboration, as well as how local governments communicate with the public and balance competing interests. Intended for college students, the discussion will emphasize access to public information, civic engagement, and the role of local governance in a democratic society. A moderated Q&A session will conclude the program.\n\nInterested in learning about Sunshine Week? Learn more here: https://sunshineweek.org/ \n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2296762
END:VEVENT
