SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:Introduction to Wood CNC Machining
LOCATION:Horizon Hall 1408 (The MIX), Fairfax, Virginia, United States
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2294727
DESCRIPTION:This workshop introduces students to the basics of CNC machining for woodworking. Participants will learn how to operate the CNC machine at the MIX for wood cutting, carving, and engraving projects.\nThe session covers essential safety procedures, basic software setup, and step-by-step instructions on how to prepare and run a job using this specific CNC machine. CAD/CAM experience is recommended but not required, just come ready to learn and create.\n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2294727
END:VEVENT
