SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:Visiting Filmmakers Series: Mahrya MacIntire with "An American Bombing: The Road to April 19th"
LOCATION:Johnson Center Cinema, Fairfax, Virginia, United States
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2295740
DESCRIPTION:Join us for a free screening of "An American Bombing An American Bombing: The Road to April 19th", followed by a Q&A with filmmaker Mahrya MacIntire\nSee event site https://vfs.gmu.edu/events/17930\n\nTwo-time Emmy nominee Mahrya MacIntire will present An American Bombing: The Road to April 19th (HBO 2024) on March 24. Our host is Sam Lebovic, GMU History and Art History and Cultural Studies Professor.\n\nOur event is free and open to the public. Registration is not required to attend. \n--\nGeorge Mason University is committed to providing access and reasonable accommodations in its services, programs, and activities. Please make accommodation requests related to a disability by contacting film@gmu.edu at least one week prior to the event. \n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2295740
END:VEVENT
