UID:b843012dc8a9dcbe23414a741569382d3192026_1:15:06_PM@campusgroups.com
SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:Peer Empowerment Program (PEP) Application 2026-2027
LOCATION: Sign in to download the location
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2297283
DESCRIPTION:Join the Peer Empowerment Program (PEP)! \nPEP’s mission is to decrease stigma and spread awareness of mental health through engaging programs, events, and social media. Receive hands-on mental health experience!\n\n- Are you passionate about spreading mental health awareness on campus?\n- Are you interested in professional growth and resume building?\n- Do you want to connect with peers with similar interests? \n\nRequirements:\n- Must be enrolled at George Mason University taking at least 3 credits\n- Must be able to commit to at least two full semesters\n- Available for weekly in-person and/or virtual meetings on Tuesdays from 3-5 PM \n\nIf you are interested in applying, kindly click on the link provided or scan the QR code below. \n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2297283
END:VEVENT
