UID:db2019ad459e7974dbd852b4824d0792372026_12:37:12_PM@campusgroups.com
SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:How to Get Funded: Scholarships, Research & Study Abroad at Mason
LOCATION:Nguyen Engineering Building, Room 1103, Fairfax, Virginia, United States
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2296890
DESCRIPTION:Interested in funding your research, studying abroad, or applying for competitive scholarships and fellowships? Join ColorStack GMU and the Office of Fellowships for an informative and student-focused session on how to unlock academic and professional opportunities beyond the classroom.\n\nThe first half of the event will feature a 30-minute informational session led by advisors from the Office of Fellowships, covering major scholarships, research funding, study abroad opportunities, application timelines, and strategies for becoming a competitive candidate.\n\nThe second half will spotlight students who have successfully pursued scholarships or study abroad experiences. They will share insights, application tips, lessons learned, and advice on how to navigate the process effectively.\n\nWhether you’re a freshman exploring options or a junior preparing applications, this session will provide practical guidance and actionable next steps.\n\nAll majors welcome. \n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2296890
END:VEVENT
