UID:c2e6886b8c4f159de4d6ee4859d97c499112025_2:22:33_PM@campusgroups.com
SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:ArtSpark: A Creative Collaboration Challenge
LOCATION:Fenwick Reading Room, Fairfax, Virginia, United States
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2288416
DESCRIPTION:ArtSpark: A Creative Collaboration Challenge \nWhere creative chaos meets artistic chemistry. \n\nReady to blow up your artistic comfort zone? \nIntroducing the ArtSpark Creative Collaboration Challenge — a one-of-a-kind event where artists, makers, crafters, and performers are randomly paired with someone from a completely different discipline to create a brand-new piece of collaborative art. Think: a sculptor + a dancer. A poet + a painter. A photographer + a puppeteer. Enjoy tasty autumn treats and warm cider as you make connections and expand your artistic horizons. \nAnd here’s the twist: every pair must incorporate a surprise library resource revealed on the day of the event.  \nIts Taskmaster meets an artistic blind date! \n\nHow It Works: \nRegister at least one week ahead of time so we can match you with your creative opposite. \nChat with your partner before the event to brainstorm your concept. \nBring whatever materials you typically use — we’ll supply some extra craft supplies just in case. \nCome to the event and create your collaborative masterpiece, incorporating the surprise library resource.  \nAll works will be showcased on the library’s Instagram. \nOne lucky pair will win a prize for best piece of art that embraces the rules of the challenge.  \n\nWho Should Join? \nArt majors? Absolutely. \nTheater kids? Definitely. \nCrochet goblins, open mic troubadours, party-trick beatboxers, collage witches, bedroom DJs, and comic doodlers? YES. \nThis isn’t just for the pros — it’s for anyone who creates anything. \n\nWhy You’ll Love It: \nMake unexpected creative connections \nLearn from other disciplines \nStretch your skills in new directions \nWalk away with a piece you never would’ve created alone \n\nBreak your bubble. Spark something weird and wonderful. \nRegister now to get paired and start planning your creative collision. \n🎭 Date: Thursday, October 2\n📍 Location: Fenwick Library Reading Room\n⏰ Time: 1:30-3:30pm\n📷 Follow the chaos: @masonlibraries\nLet the collaboration chaos begin. \n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2288416
END:VEVENT
