UID:8b789e67bcaf03d8e54b10f5f245515d2182026_1:26:41_PM@campusgroups.com
SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:Visiting Filmmakers Series: Class Visit - Mahrya MacIntire with "Muscle Memory"
LOCATION:AB 1007, Fairfax, Virginia, United States
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2296082
DESCRIPTION:MacIntire’s work-in-progress Muscle Memory, talks about processing both trauma and neurodivergence through movement and somatic practices. It features some "nontraditional" camera placements, editing, and sound techniques. It also provides an opportunity to talk about things like overwhelm and anxiety on set, and potential coping strategies.\n\n*Limited seats available\n\nFor more information: https://vfs.gmu.edu/events/18037\n\n--\nGeorge Mason University is committed to providing access and reasonable accommodations in its services, programs, and activities. Please make accommodation requests related to a disability by contacting film@gmu.edu at least one week prior to the event. \n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2296082
END:VEVENT
