SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:Breaking Barriers: Women Leading the Future of Tech
LOCATION:Planetary Hall, Room 127, Fairfax, Virginia, United States
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2296954
DESCRIPTION:Join ColorStack GMU for a Women in Tech panel in celebration of Women’s History Month. This event will bring together industry professionals across software engineering, UX, consulting, and cybersecurity to share their career journeys, challenges, and advice for students entering the tech industry.\n\nPanelists will discuss topics such as navigating internships, building confidence in male-dominated spaces, breaking into competitive tech roles, and creating meaningful impact through technology. Students will also have the opportunity to ask questions and gain insights on career growth, technical development, and leadership.\n\nWhether you’re exploring careers in tech or looking for guidance on the next steps in your journey, this event is a great opportunity to learn from and connect with women making an impact in the industry.\n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2296954
END:VEVENT
