UID:28c2da7648b72c669e75ef7ff154866d362026_12:47:01_AM@campusgroups.com
SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:Mason Korea : MK-MUN Special Lecture by Professor Cox
LOCATION:Matz Hall (G101), Fairfax, Virginia, United States
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2296865
DESCRIPTION:The United Nations (UN) has made expanding political participation, equality, and human rights central pillars of its development and peacebuilding agendas. Yet compounding global challenges, including democratic backsliding, armed conflict, and climate change, among others, have created obstacles to UN efforts to promote the core values of democracy. This talk examines the foundations of UN democracy assistance, how the organization has adapted to these challenges, and the tradeoffs it faces in promoting democratic governance today.\n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2296865
END:VEVENT
