UID:eec2510d5a2178009353c0b5812246833242026_10:27:43_AM@campusgroups.com
SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:Printed Circuit Board (PCB) Fabrication
LOCATION:Horizon Hall 1408, Fairfax, Virginia, United States
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2297439
DESCRIPTION:This 1‑hour workshop immerses participants in PCB fabrication through direct, hands‑on use of the Bantam PCB Mill, moving from exported Gerber files to a milled board. After a brief overview, the session is spent actively preparing, leveling, and machining a real PCB while learning the fundamentals of CNC milling, PCB materials, and basic electronics. It’s a highly interactive class designed to get attendees working with real tools and real boards right away. Participants should ideally have taken a PCB design class (also offered at the MIX) or have introductory-level knowledge. Soldering experience is recommended.\n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2297439
END:VEVENT
