UID:f302609a33b80b94dbb01d4eaca6491d12172025_2:13:22_PM@campusgroups.com
SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:Intro to Camping at Westmoreland State Park
LOCATION:TBD
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2291946
DESCRIPTION:Spend the weekend with Outdoor Adventures as we leave campus behind and travel to Virginia’s Northern Neck on the banks of the Potomac River for some hiking, shark tooth hunting, and tent camping.  We’ll spend Saturday morning packing for the night, then drive to the state park which features the Fossil Beach, where fossilized remnants of ancient shark teeth can be found, before returning to the campsite for a hearty dinner and a night spent under the stars.\n\nDifficulty: Beginner – This trip requires walking over rocky, uneven ground, and sleeping on a sleeping pad in a tent on the ground.  The hiking distance is relatively manageable for beginners, with the total hiking being less than 3 miles each day \n\nAmenities: Bathhouse located in the campground\n\nTravel Time: 2 hours each way \n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2291946
END:VEVENT
