DTSTART:20260328T220000Z
DTEND:20260329T013000Z
UID:055eb3e9486af52cbc548e0cb26ebd2c2172026_3:20:41_PM@campusgroups.com
SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:Iranian Nowrouz
LOCATION:JC Dewberry Hall , Fairfax, Virginia, United States
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2296039
DESCRIPTION:We are coming together as a community to celebrate the arrival of our New Year—a sacred moment of renewal, rebirth, and fresh beginnings. This is a time when we gather around shared traditions, honor our cultural heritage, and welcome the promise of brighter days ahead. The New Year reminds us of resilience: of spring following even the harshest winter, of light returning after darkness, and of hope persisting despite hardship. It is a celebration of life, unity, and the enduring strength that binds us together across generations and borders.\n\nAt the same time, we pause in reflection and remembrance. As we step into a new chapter, we carry in our hearts the memory of those who have tragically lost their lives. We honor them not only with silence, but with intention—by speaking their names, by sharing their stories, and by committing ourselves to the values they stood for. Our gathering holds both joy and sorrow, celebration and tribute. It is in this balance that we find meaning.\n\nThrough this event, we embrace our culture, our traditions, and our collective resilience, while paying heartfelt tribute to those who are no longer with us. We stand together in solidarity, drawing strength from one another, determined that their memories will not fade and that their legacy will continue to inspire courage, compassion, and hope in the year ahead.\nDress Code: Casual (jeans ok)\n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2296039
END:VEVENT
