UID:78c21ee0258be235fa61ac5183401a003162026_2:03:51_AM@campusgroups.com
SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:Movie Night 
LOCATION:Student Union I, 3A, Meeting Room, Fairfax, Virginia, United States
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2297071
DESCRIPTION:The members will be watching a public domain radiation documentary/short historical clips on YouTube. This documentary/clips will allow members to learn more about radiation, its history, and its safety issues that arose back then. More specifically, the videos found under public domain and with no license needed, consisting of historical video archives will be about the Radium Girls history. The flyer states radiation documentary / movie night to get more people intrigued but will likely consists of short history clips/ clips such as "Duck and Cover" that are public domain. Members will be able to relax and watch the clips, while eating. The food idea is to have popcorn bags from Giant, not the microwave type. As well as have boba for members to drink on while watching the movie.\nDress Code: Casual (jeans ok)\n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2297071
END:VEVENT
