SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:Intro to Machine Learning Workshop: Building a Handwritten Digit Classifier
LOCATION:The HUB, Meeting Room 2, Fairfax, Virginia, United States
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2297583
DESCRIPTION:Join us for a hands-on introduction to machine learning! In this workshop, we’ll train a neural network to recognize handwritten digits using Python. Along the way, you'll learn key data science and machine learning concepts such as training and validation datasets, neural networks, and model predictions.\n\nWe’ll be working with popular tools like NumPy, Pandas, Scikit-learn, and TensorFlow inside a Google Colab notebook. No prior machine learning experience is required—this workshop is designed for beginners who want to see how real ML models are built and trained.\n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2297583
END:VEVENT
