UID:6ab634f8eff967cfccb0b1324de5be34182026_1:57:46_PM@campusgroups.com
SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:An Evening with Grant Thornton: Careers & Opportunities
LOCATION: Sign in to download the location
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2292222
DESCRIPTION:Beta Alpha Psi Theta Alpha presents an exclusive networking event with Grant Thornton, one of the nation's leading audit, tax, and advisory firms.\n\nGrant Thornton offers the reach and resources of a global firm with the culture and accessibility of a mid-size environment. Their professionals work with dynamic organizations—from ambitious startups to established Fortune 500 companies.\n\nJoin us to connect with Grant Thornton recruiters and professionals who will share insights on:\n- Career paths in audit, tax, and advisory services\n- What sets Grant Thornton apart from the Big Four\n- Internship and full-time opportunities\n- Interview tips and recruiting timelines\n\nThis is your chance to explore an alternative to the Big Four that consistently ranks among the best places to work in accounting.\n\n📅 Wednesday, April 1, 2026\n🕐 5:00 PM - 6:30 PM\n📍 Johnson Center - Georges\n👔 Business Professional Attire\n🍕 Food Provided\n\nOpen to all Beta Alpha Psi members and prospective candidates. RSVP required.\n\nQuestions? Contact bap@gmu.edu\nDress Code: Business Casual\n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2292222
END:VEVENT
