UID:54cca9ff0b561215534c4a2ac6b3e7303232026_5:04:59_AM@campusgroups.com
SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:MK Mental Health Talks II: Self-Care that Actually Works
LOCATION:Mason Korea G316, Fairfax, Virginia, United States
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2297377
DESCRIPTION:You’re invited to MK Mental Health Talks II: Self-Care that Actually Works on Thursday, April 2 at 12:00 PM in G316.\n\nThis session is designed to move beyond the common idea of self-care as simply relaxation and instead help students understand what actually supports their well-being in a sustainable way. Students will reflect on what truly recharges them, explore practical self-care strategies that fit their real lives, and consider how to make small, meaningful changes over time.\n\nLunch will be provided for students who RSVP in advance. Walk-ins are welcome, but lunch cannot be guaranteed without an RSVP.\n\nWe hope you’ll join us for this honest and practical conversation about self-care that actually works.\n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2297377
END:VEVENT
