UID:923c077fb7be0cfe4e349855db2f3fe6172026_2:51:50_PM@campusgroups.com
SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:Interviewing in the U.S. Workshop featuring Argon Accounting
LOCATION:Online Event
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2292184
DESCRIPTION:Join us for Interviewing in the U.S. featuring Aida Davalos, Director of Accounting at Argon Accounting LLC.\n\nNavigating the U.S. job market as an international student comes with its own unique challenges—especially when it comes to interviews. This workshop is designed to help you feel more confident and prepared as you take on job or internship interviews in an American workplace setting. \n\nOur career advising team will offer helpful tips and practical guidance to support your success in U.S.-based interviews. Whether you’re just getting started or actively applying, this workshop is a valuable opportunity to learn what to expect and how to position yourself as a strong candidate. \n\nThis workshop takes place via Zoom. Pre-registration required.\n \nQuestions? Contact Costello College of Business Office of Career Services at mycareer@gmu.edu or 703-993-2140. \n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2292184
END:VEVENT
