UID:8be7ecde817d5547d0563704417a31743172026_10:59:58_PM@campusgroups.com
SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:Passover Seder (Night 2!) for Jewish GMU Students
LOCATION: Sign in to download the location
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2297190
DESCRIPTION:Jewish people celebrate not one, but two Passover seders each year! This is the grand event for the second Passover Seder on April 2nd. The Seder is THE place to be for Jewish people worldwide, and GMU students are no exception! We will be having a grand Seder, complete with all 15 traditional steps and an absolutely delicious and lavish meal. We'll be singing all of the traditional seder songs, giving out props for the 10 plagues, and so much more. \nThe Seder is the traditional Passover meal that includes reading, telling stories, eating special foods, singing, and other Passover traditions.\n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2297190
END:VEVENT
