UID:9e589c66519d2186a0f5aa797ab7853f1112026_8:02:59_AM@campusgroups.com
SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:Cultural Studies 2026 Student Symposium
LOCATION:Fenwick Library Main Reading Room, Fairfax, Virginia, United States
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2292370
DESCRIPTION: \nThe Cultural Studies Student Symposium, entitled "Reimagined Futures: Anti-Colonial World-Making and Cultural Practice," will feature a keynote address by Dr. Talawa Adodo on decolonial praxis and culture from 10 am to 11 am. There will be three panels of student presentations, one in the morning and two in the afternoon. After the keynote and presentations, they will be able to ask the presenters questions and engage with other students in discourse on the presentation topics. Breakfast and lunch will be provided. \n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2292370
END:VEVENT
