UID:f1e1771ee72beeb74266c918f9e7ec0711212025_11:14:06_AM@campusgroups.com
SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:Spring into Service Friday Volunteer Event
LOCATION:Sci Tech Campus in Manassas, Green and White Tent, 38°45'29.4"N,77°31'15.3"W
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2291604
DESCRIPTION:Kickoff the warming weather with outdoor community service. Come join us to spend time caring for the Piedmont Trail, a 1.2-mile loop that winds through a quiet forested wetland in Manassas, located on Mason’s SciTech Campus. \n\nWhile you clear trails, spread mulch, and pick up trash, you can expect to see deer, birds, squirrels, and possibly even turtles!\n\nYour service keeps the Piedmont Trail accessible for 1,000s of visitors each year! It’s a simple way to make a big impact.\n\nMeet us at the green and white tent by the Freedom Aquatic and Fitness Center\n\nSnacks and drinks will be available for volunteers who RSVP\n\nNeed a ride? Mason students, staff, and faculty can take the Mason Shuttle. Depart Sandy Creek Transit Center on Fairfax Campus at 11:50am to arrive on time. Depart Colgan Hall on SciTech Campus at 3:20p or 5:10p to return to Fairfax.\nDress Code: Casual (jeans ok)\n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2291604
END:VEVENT
