UID:7c2b134287e60faf223682e703c98d0b12172025_2:18:43_PM@campusgroups.com
SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:Hike to Signal Knob
LOCATION:TBD
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2291951
DESCRIPTION:Signal Knob is one of the most challenging—and rewarding—hikes in the Massanutten Mountains. This classic ridge loop features sweeping overlooks of the Shenandoah Valley, rocky climbs, and miles of scenic ridgelines. The summit was once a Civil War lookout point, offering historic significance alongside stunning views. \n\nDifficulty: Advanced – Expect a strenuous 10-mile loop with steep, rocky ascents and long descents. Good physical conditioning recommended. \n\nAmenities: Portable toilets available at the trailhead \n\nTravel Time: 1 hour and 15 minutes each way \n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2291951
END:VEVENT
