UID:3c5815cd4dc62717c48ab7c578e80d061292025_1:21:52_PM@campusgroups.com
SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:Real Talk: Religious Expression in the Job Search & Workplace
LOCATION:Fenwick A, Room A110, 4400 University Drive, Fairfax 22030, United States
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2291813
DESCRIPTION:This workshop is designed to help students and recent graduates navigate their professional journeys while honoring their faith and values. We'll explore how to choose a career path that aligns with your religious identity, ask for accommodations during the interview process, and foster inclusive dialogue with colleagues. This interactive discussion aims to equip you with the knowledge and confidence to approach your career effectively, respecting both your religious expression and professional responsibilities. \n\nThis event is open to all George Mason students and alumni.\n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2291813
END:VEVENT
