UID:eeb94ceadcf90aa855a35b244e82bae83302026_10:26:30_AM@campusgroups.com
SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:QT Autism Diagnosis Q&A
LOCATION: Sign in to download the location
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2297699
DESCRIPTION:Getting an autism diagnosis can be really overwhelming and challenging, especially as an adult and as a queer person. Services for adults can be hard to access and often have long waitlists. It can also be challenging to find affirming services.\n\nGMU and Children's National Hospital are recruiting participants for a study on late diagnosis of autism. We're interested in understanding why some people are diagnosed with autism later in life. We also want to learn how someone’s identities and life experiences can influence their experience of autism. As part of the study, you can receive an autism evaluation by a trained clinical psychologist at Children's National at no cost to you. If a research diagnosis is received, you will get a report with your diagnosis information. \n\nYou may also learn about what the process of getting an autism diagnosis is like and about autism services in the area. Join us for a Q&A style panel to learn more.\n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2297699
END:VEVENT
