UID:f1f33aa6122a35f07713acd6d70fa8bb2252026_7:00:30_PM@campusgroups.com
SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:Praxis Strategies Workshop: Elementary Ed Math and Science
LOCATION:Online Event
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2296516
DESCRIPTION:Calling all future elementary and early childhood teachers!  Do you want to build confidence for your upcoming Praxis math and science exams? Please join us for an hands-on workshop based on Praxis subtests 5003 and 5005 (part of the Elementary Education: Multiple Subject 5001 exam). During this session, we will explain how to create and stick to a study plan and how to employ effective study strategies for reviewing math and science concepts.  We will explore test-taking tips using sample problems from the official Praxis study guides and other resources, and we'll outline what to expect on test day. Lastly, we will discuss ways of coping with test anxiety and self-doubt.  We hope you can join us for the virtual session. \n\nMeeting Link: https://gmu.zoom.us/s/94944535876\n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2296516
END:VEVENT
