UID:7317e29caf0854b6cf9074e41664ddc912172025_2:19:24_PM@campusgroups.com
SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:Intro to Backpacking: Sky Meadows State Park
LOCATION:TBD
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2291952
DESCRIPTION:Dip your toes into the world of backpacking on this beautiful overnight trip through Sky Meadows State Park. With rolling hills, open meadows, and quiet forested trails, this location is the perfect beginner-friendly setting to learn backpacking skills like packing, camp cooking, and proper trail etiquette. Enjoy a peaceful night under the stars as you gain confidence carrying everything you need on your back. \n\nDifficulty: Beginner – Expect to hike 3–5 miles each day while carrying a pack weighing 25–35 lbs. Trails include moderate inclines and grassy paths. \n\nAmenities: Campsite has portable toilets; no running water \n\nTravel Time: 1 hour and 15 minutes each way \n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2291952
END:VEVENT
