UID:a695f88aa0127dfccd66cdfbaf91963a12172025_2:20:15_PM@campusgroups.com
SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:Outdoor Climbing: Sugarloaf Mountain
LOCATION:TBD
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2291953
DESCRIPTION:Spend the day climbing on the scenic cliffs of Sugarloaf Mountain! This area offers routes for every ability level, including steep crack climbs and beginner-friendly jug-filled routes. Whether it’s your first day on real rock or you’re an experienced climber looking to push yourself, this outing is a great way to enjoy the spring weather and build your skills outdoors. \n\nDifficulty: Beginner–Intermediate – Routes range from easy slabs to more technical faces and small overhangs. All equipment provided. \n\nAmenities: Restrooms available at the parking area \n\nTravel Time: 1 hour and 15 minutes each way \n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2291953
END:VEVENT
