UID:96100291c5a72510628fe2f95af97a803242026_2:47:26_PM@campusgroups.com
SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:Intro to After Effects & Motions
LOCATION:Horizon Hall 1410 (check in 1408), Fairfax, Virginia, United States
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2297461
DESCRIPTION:This 1‑hour, hands‑on workshop introduces participants to Adobe After Effects, focusing on what the software is used for and how it differs from Premiere Pro. Attendees will learn the basics of navigation, keyframes, and transform tools as they create a simple animation of a soccer ball moving toward a goal. Most of the session is spent directly inside After Effects, experimenting with images, motion, and small details that bring animations to life. It’s an accessible, beginner‑friendly class designed to make motion graphics feel intuitive and fun.\n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2297461
END:VEVENT
