UID:369240ff88aa18a3b1cf86b7696993ed3232026_8:06:43_PM@campusgroups.com
SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:Environmentalism in Latin America
LOCATION:SUB 1 3A, Fairfax, Virginia, United States
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2297417
DESCRIPTION:The Latin American Political Society (LAPS) invites students to attend Environmentalism in Latin America, an engaging event focused on the environmental challenges shaping the region today. This discussion will explore key issues such as deforestation in the Amazon, climate change, resource extraction, and environmental justice movements led by Indigenous and local communities. Through real-world examples and open conversation, attendees will gain insight into how environmental issues are deeply connected to politics, economic systems, and social inequalities in Latin America. The event encourages students to think critically about global sustainability and the role of activism, while also providing a space to share perspectives and learn from others. Whether you are passionate about environmental issues or simply interested in learning more, this event offers a meaningful opportunity to engage, reflect, and connect with topics that impact both Latin America and the world.\nDress Code: Business Casual\n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2297417
END:VEVENT
