UID:e3f8e193a36dc369203ca1745d2480673222026_11:40:33_AM@campusgroups.com
SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:Discussion on Morality, Justice, and the Pursuit of Peace
LOCATION:Johnson Center, 333, Meeting Room D, Fairfax Campus, Fairfax, Virginia, United States
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2297359
DESCRIPTION:A moderated panel discussion exploring morality, justice, and the pursuit of peace, followed by an open audience Q&A. The panel will feature an Imam from the Ahmadiyya Muslim Community alongside faculty speakers from George Mason University, bringing together religious and academic perspectives for a thoughtful conversation.\n\nIn a time marked by polarization, social tension, and global conflict, there is a growing need for thoughtful dialogue on how moral frameworks shape laws, institutions, and human behavior. This discussion will explore the relationship between ethical principles, the idea of justice, and the conditions necessary for lasting peace in society.\n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2297359
END:VEVENT
