UID:164d47ffbd83c29ba159b24e35ec2b673132026_3:45:52_PM@campusgroups.com
SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:WastED: Mason Dining's Sustainability Spotlight Series
LOCATION:The Spot, Fairfax, Virginia, United States
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2297017
DESCRIPTION:Join us for a sustainability showcase that brings together Mason students, faculty, and campus groups for an evening of inspiring talks, good food, and hands‑on ideas for creating change. Come explore projects happening across Mason and learn how you can get involved in building a more sustainable campus.\n\nWe are excited to feature two faculty speakers, Dr. Kerri LaCharite and Dr. Jennifer Sklarew, as well as the VP of Sustainability for Chartwells Higher Ed, Monalisa Prasad. \n\nThe event will take place on April 14 from 5:00pm - 8:00pm at The Spot. \n\n5:00 - 6:00: Connect with GMU organizations while enjoying sustainable mocktails and hors d'oeuvres. We will also have DIY pickles, coffee scrubs made from upcycled coffee grounds and sample jars of honey from our campus hives!\n6:00 - 7:00: Speaker Spotlights \n7:00 - 8:00: Continue building connections \n\nDress Code: Casual (jeans ok)\n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2297017
END:VEVENT
