UID:a4412844505a7104101219eb97893c4a472026_1:45:06_PM@campusgroups.com
SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:Reli Deli 
LOCATION:Horizon Hall 6323 , Fairfax, Virginia, United States
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2298048
DESCRIPTION:https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSfnb8cKXspVUrL1kEAgGb0EPkFAiN8xmd2PXUL9vg7qsiy5Eg/viewform \n\nThe RELI Deli is for any student interested in the academic study of religion. You don't need to be a RELI major or minor. You don't need to be taking a RELI class this semester. You really only need to like two things: food and talking about religion. Those two things go together extremely well. And we provide the food. \n\nOn April 15th our guest is Dr. Tal Vaizman, who is a postdoctoral fellow in the Department of Religious Studies. He will talk about how studying contemporary music teaches us about religion and culture. \n\nThis month we're meeting in Horizon Hall 6323 (6th floor kitchen space) at 12:00. We're done by 1:00. \n\nSign up quickly! This is limited to around 20 students. You'll get a confirmation email from me that we have reserved space for you. \n\nThe food will be from Fairfax Kabob. \nDress Code: Casual (jeans ok)\n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2298048
END:VEVENT
