UID:7703cd1cd98bd67a8e2052014faaacd7242026_1:36:12_PM@campusgroups.com
SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:Metal CNC Machining 
LOCATION:Horizon Hall 1408 - The MIX, Fairfax, Virginia, United States
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2295073
DESCRIPTION:Learn the fundamentals of precision metal machining using CNC mills and routers. This hands-on workshop covers material selection, toolpath generation, feeds and speeds optimization, and safe machine operation. Participants will gain practical experience setting up jobs, selecting appropriate cutting tools, and producing accurate metal parts. Basic CAD/CAM knowledge is preferred but not required. Ideal for students and makers looking to expand their fabrication capabilities beyond wood and plastics.\nDress Code: Casual (jeans ok)\n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2295073
END:VEVENT
