UID:60ade18e47d1cccb88f65988b76098523232026_3:07:20_PM@campusgroups.com
SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:Fund for the Public Interest Info Session
LOCATION:Student Union 1 Building, Room 3311, 4400 University Drive, Fairfax, VA 22030, United States
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2297399
DESCRIPTION:Make a difference for pollinators, old growth forests, and fight plastic pollution this summer!  Join Fund for the Public Interest and talk with a director about working on a campaign that engages citizens directly. Their canvassers talk to people one-on-one and make thousands of peoples voices heard through petitions, donations, emails, and meetings.  Together, you can make a real impact on our environment, our democracy, and beyond. Stop by their info session and chat with them to learn more!\n\nInformation sessions will be held at 10:00 am, 1:30 pm, and 3:30 pm with interviews to follow after each information session.\nDress Code: Business Casual\n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2297399
END:VEVENT
