UID:5511572aad52541196cb2fd44a7837b21142026_1:09:49_PM@campusgroups.com
SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:The EDGE - Spring Open Climb (Giant Swing)  
LOCATION:The EDGE Alpine Tower, Mason SciTech Campus, 10960 George Mason Cir, Manassas, VA 20109, United States
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2292825
DESCRIPTION:Fly through the air with the greatest of ease! Bring your friends--you will work as a team to lift your fellow participants as high as 30 feet off the ground. When it's your turn, choose your starting height, then pull the rip cord for a brief free-fall and a thrilling swing through the open air.  \n\nNo prior experience is needed. Just bring your sense of adventure! \n\nNeed transportation? A dedicated van pool is available for the 4:00 time slot. Seats are limited. The van pool will meet on Fairfax campus (the RAC) at 2:45 pm. If van registration is full, you can reach SciTech using the free Mason shuttle. Check the Spring 2026 schedule for departure times. \n\nAccessibility: Participants of all abilities are welcome. Please reach out to us at least 2 weeks prior to discuss accommodations, such as closer parking or adaptive options. edge@gmu.edu\nDress Code: Casual (jeans ok)\n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2292825
END:VEVENT
