UID:e262fd8058a425209b4e06ead870874112172025_2:23:01_PM@campusgroups.com
SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:Intro to Mountain Biking: Laurel Hill
LOCATION:TBD
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2291955
DESCRIPTION:Experience the thrill of off-road biking at Laurel Hill! This beginner-friendly trail system offers wooded singletrack, gentle berms, rolling hills, and plenty of opportunities to build confidence. Trip leaders will teach braking, shifting, handling, and how to safely ride trail features before venturing onto the loop. \n\nDifficulty: Beginner – Previous biking experience required; no mountain biking experience needed. Expect roots, small hills, and gradual progression throughout the day. \n\nAmenities: Portable toilets are available at the trailhead \n\nTravel Time: 30 minutes each way   \n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2291955
END:VEVENT
