DESCRIPTION:Mason Neck State Park is one of the region’s most peaceful spring hiking destinations. Explore forested paths, wetlands, and riverfront trails while learning about the area’s rich bird and wildlife habitat. This is a perfect outing for beginner hikers or anyone looking for a scenic, low-stress adventure. \n\nDifficulty: Beginner – Mostly flat terrain with gentle hills; expect to hike 4–6 miles. \n \nAmenities: Indoor restrooms available at the Visitor Center \n\nTravel Time: 30 minutes each way   \n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2291956
