UID:5a300d00a064252ffaa1a72ed33c2f73172026_3:13:14_PM@campusgroups.com
SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:Resume 101: Basics & Formatting Workshop featuring LandCare
LOCATION:Online Event
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2292195
DESCRIPTION:Join us for a resume writing workshop featuring Lindsay Stup, Talent Acquisition Specialist at LandCare - a commercial landscape company hiring student for business roles! \n\nIn this hands-on session, tailored for Costello College of Business students, our expert career advisors will guide you through the foundational elements of creating a polished, professional resume. You’ll learn how to structure your resume for maximum impact, choose the right format for your career goals, and ensure your document is visually appealing and easy to read.\n\nKey Takeaways:\n-Understand the essential components of a strong resume layout.\n-Learn formatting best practices to make your resume stand out.\n-Discover how to organize sections for clarity and professionalism.\n-This virtual workshop takes place on Zoom. Pre-registration required.\n \nQuestions? Contact Costello College of Business Office of Career Services at mycareer@gmu.edu or 703-993-2140. \n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2292195
END:VEVENT
