UID:e98afce049de7bd7c474f2a4d470a4a0242026_1:48:12_PM@campusgroups.com
SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:Arduino Intermediate Workshop
LOCATION:Horizon Hall 1408, Fairfax, Virginia, United States
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2295085
DESCRIPTION:This workshop builds on the Introduction to the the Arduino open source I/O microcontroller platform for the creation of robotic, sensor-based projects, and any other creative application you can dream up. This workshop focuses on the relationship between sensor input and component output as well as servo motors and libraries within the Arduino environment. This workshop also builds on methods for programming hardware that can apply to other software development languages.\nDress Code: Casual (jeans ok)\n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2295085
END:VEVENT
