UID:7961df51a5de740424e09a81da7c13673312026_3:23:45_PM@campusgroups.com
SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:Sips & Scholars: The Women Who Watched: One Generation's Witness
LOCATION:Fuse, Room 1327, 3401 Fairfax Dr, Arlington 22201, United States
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2297790
DESCRIPTION:You’re invited to go behind the glass with Author Supriya Baily. In the late 1980s, they were schoolgirls in a burgeoning middle class; today, they are the witnesses to a city’s political turn. Come explore the "Silicon Valley of India" through the eyes of the women who lived its history. We’ll discuss the erosion of freedom, the rise of the right-wing, and the resilient spirit of the Bangalore Girls.\nDress Code: Casual (jeans ok)\n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2297790
END:VEVENT
