UID:7dee3e2fd177147cb7a58bce56cf0ecd3152026_8:28:29_PM@campusgroups.com
SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:Dominos with the Lambdas
LOCATION:JC Gold, United States
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2297057
DESCRIPTION:Join us for Dominos with the Lambdas, a fun and engaging event where culture, history, and community come together! Attendees will get the chance to explore the rich history of dominos, a game deeply rooted in Latin and Caribbean traditions, and learn how it has been used for generations as a way to bring people together. We will walk through the origins of the game, its cultural significance, and how it continues to be a staple in many households and social spaces today.\n\nWhether you’re a beginner or already know how to play, this event will include a step-by-step breakdown of the rules of dominos, strategies to improve your game, and plenty of time for hands-on play. Members of Lambda Theta Phi will guide participants through the basics and create a welcoming, interactive environment where everyone can learn and have fun.\n\nThis event is perfect for anyone looking to connect with others, learn something new, and experience a piece of culture through friendly competition. Come ready to play, laugh, and build community—no experience needed!\n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2297057
END:VEVENT
