UID:eb9a389724c6c10025152b21ce9a430a3272026_2:20:07_PM@campusgroups.com
SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:Multimeter Basics Workshop
LOCATION:Horizon Hall 1408, Fairfax, Virginia, United States
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2297603
DESCRIPTION:This 1‑hour, hands‑on workshop introduces beginners to the fundamentals of using a multimeter to measure voltage, resistance, and current. Participants will practice connecting a multimeter to premade circuits, learning how to set it up correctly and identify faulty components through guided demonstrations. Most of the session is spent actively testing real circuits to build confidence and accuracy. It’s a practical, beginner‑friendly class designed to show how simple and useful multimeters can be for troubleshooting everyday electronics.\n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2297603
END:VEVENT
