UID:87254026a7e158ff516e652cfa3abdc11232026_1:48:13_PM@campusgroups.com
SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:HackRF: Workshop with James Hope
LOCATION:Horizon Hall 1408, Fairfax, Virginia, United States
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2294167
DESCRIPTION:Within this workshop, each participant is loaned an RTL-SDR and be instructed on the basics of SDR++ software. Subjects would include the waveform, how to identify and find radio signals, how to move throughout the spectrum, and how to demodulate and listen to a radio station. Instructor will also demonstrate transmitting and have participants find and demodulate the signal that is transmited. Example projects involving SDR like my NOAA satellite antenna and the images captured using it will be demonstrated. Some satellites images obtained via the Hack RF will be shared for participants to better understand the impacts of different weather patterns on quality of data transmission.\n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2294167
END:VEVENT
