UID:84d47a4517cda08e969029e56b865c7a2122026_2:32:26_PM@campusgroups.com
SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:Career Coaching Day for Korean International Student
LOCATION:Johnson Center, Georges, Fairfax, Virginia, United States
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2295729
DESCRIPTION:This career coaching day event is designed to support Korean international students at Mason as they navigate their academic and professional futures in the United States and beyond. The session will provide practical guidance on CPT and OPT processes, work authorization regulations, and job search strategies in the U.S.\n\nIn addition, the event will explore long-term career planning for students who are considering opportunities both in the United States and South Korea. Topics will include resume and interview preparation across cultural contexts, differences in hiring practices between the two countries, and strategies for building a competitive global profile.\n\nThis event aims to empower Korean students to make informed decisions about their career paths, strengthen their confidence as international professionals, and build a supportive community where students can share experiences and resources.\nDress Code: Business Casual\n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2295729
END:VEVENT
