UID:925cfbd6a79d489e8bafe70c92a1bff13312026_2:01:07_PM@campusgroups.com
SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:Albanian Culture Club Meeting
LOCATION:FENWCK A110 , Fairfax, Virginia, United States
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2297778
DESCRIPTION:On this meeting day we will have special guest dancer/performer demonstrate Albanian dance and folk music. \n\nAlbania is a majority Muslim country in Southern European, however a significant percentage of Albanians also practice Catholicism or follow the eastern Orthodox Church. Despite its religious diversity, there is very little in the way of interfaith conflict - it is a place where religious pluralism exists peacefully. (https://www.bbc.com/travel/article/20161024-the-worlds-most-tolerant-country)\n\nThe 'valle' in Albania has deep religious, spiritual, and cultural significance. Different valle are performed for different religious ceremonies and holidays, and vary depending on region (which often times is also associated with a certain faith). \n\nIn instructing students on Albanian valle (and it's history) we will promote increased religious literacy on campus and increase student spiritual and religious worldview. The Albanian valle is much more than dance - it represents the peaceful coexistence of different faiths within a single nation.\nDress Code: Casual (jeans ok)\n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2297778
END:VEVENT
