UID:933e852f98e063a0b50b3f7a7efa58533192026_10:52:24_AM@campusgroups.com
SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:HGSO Sympsoium 
LOCATION:Merton Hall 1202, Fairfax, Virginia, United States
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2297275
DESCRIPTION:The History Graduate Student Symposium invites all history-lovers to join us for a day of exciting and interesting projects. Hear students present about their work and learn something new! Audience members will hear twenty-minute presentations from GMU history students during four different hour and a half panels. After each group of presentations, audience members are invited to ask questions to the presenters. There will be two panels in the morning and two panels in the afternoon, with a one hour break from 12pm-1pm for lunch. The panel are titled Digital Methods, the American South, Contested Narratives and Archival Silences, and More Than a Buzzword: Critical Approaches to Race in\nHistorical Narratives. This event will introduce the Mason community to students' history research, and provide a look into applications of historical thinking outside the classroom. \nDress Code: Business Casual\n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2297275
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
