UID:f930b91448a07150b2d57d3e6a4c971912172025_2:27:54_PM@campusgroups.com
SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:Outdoor Climbing: Sugarloaf Mountain
LOCATION:TBD
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2291962
DESCRIPTION:Wrap up the semester with a full day of outdoor climbing at Sugarloaf Mountain! This crag features a variety of top-rope routes perfect for everyone from new climbers to seasoned regulars. Enjoy a spring day on real rock as you challenge yourself, learn new skills, and take in stunning views of the surrounding forests. \n\nDifficulty: Beginner–Intermediate – Routes vary widely, with options for new climbers and harder challenges for experienced participants. \n\nAmenities: Restrooms available at the parking area \n\nTravel Time: 1 hour and 15 minutes each way \n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2291962
END:VEVENT
