UID:3655a4b39a45a525c03321c4ca12d4813132026_2:51:28_PM@campusgroups.com
SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:Teacher Appreciation Day Panel and Networking Event
LOCATION:Merten Hall Room 1203, United States
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2297013
DESCRIPTION:This collaborative alumni event will celebrate educators and the impact they have on shaping and inspiring future generations. The program is being organized in partnership with George Mason University Career Services, the College of Education and Human Development Alumni Chapter, the Latino Alumni Chapter, and the Black Alumni Chapter at George Mason University. The event will feature a panel of alumni educators from diverse backgrounds who share a common mission—to educate, mentor, and uplift our youth.\n\nThe program will include a moderated panel discussion highlighting the experiences and perspectives of alumni working in education, followed by opportunities for attendees to network and connect with fellow alumni and friends of Mason before and after the program. The goal of the event is to foster meaningful dialogue, celebrate the work of educators, and strengthen connections across alumni communities. \n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2297013
END:VEVENT
