SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:Mason Korea : MKMUN Special Lecture By Professor Kanji - China and The Global Legal Order
LOCATION:Matz Hall (G101), Fairfax, Virginia, United States
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2298144
DESCRIPTION:China's accession to the WTO was initially viewed as a pathway to deeper economic integration and eventual political liberalization. However, rising trade tensions and shifting global dynamics have cast doubt on these expectations. Professor Kanji examines China's evolving role within the global legal and economic order.\n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2298144
