UID:ab9114432cfd9ab6ba22dc48d04b2d8a332026_12:47:03_PM@campusgroups.com
SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:2026 Mason Film Festival & FAVS at 20 – Day 1: Student Screenings
LOCATION:Harris Theatre, Fairfax, Virginia, United States
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2296734
DESCRIPTION:The Mason Film Festival is an annual film festival at George Mason University showcasing the diverse work of Film and Video Studies students. This year, the festival will take place over two days, Friday, May 8th and Saturday, May 9th.   \n \nThe event is free and open to the public.  Each attendee must have their own separate reservation for each separate event.  Seating is extremely limited and is first come, first served. \n\nGeorge Mason University is committed to providing access and reasonable accommodations in its services, programs, and activities. Please make accommodation requests related to a disability by contacting film@gmu.edu at least one week prior to the event.\n\nIn order to increase accessibility for all audiences, all films screened in this year's Festival will have open captions (captioning featured on screen). \n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2296734
END:VEVENT
