UID:11e00405b6f17535977dfb6daaff171b332026_4:09:37_PM@campusgroups.com
SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:Mason Film Festival 2026 & FAVS at 20 – Day 2: Advanced Fiction Filmmaking Showcase
LOCATION:Harris Theatre, Fairfax, Virginia, United States
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2296754
DESCRIPTION:The Mason Film Festival is an annual film festival at George Mason University showcasing the diverse work of Film and Video Studies students, including that of beginning video students, intermediate directing students, and graduating seniors. This year, the festival will take place over two days, Friday, May 8th and Saturday, May 9th.   \n\nDay 2 will feature the FAVS 475 Advanced Fiction Filmmaking Showcase.\n \nFree and open to the public\nRegistration is required\n\nEach attendee must have their own separate reservation for each separate festival event.  \n\nSeating is extremely limited and is first come, first served. \nA wristband will be given at check-in and is required to enter in and out of the theatre.\n\nGeorge Mason University is committed to providing access and reasonable accommodations in its services, programs, and activities. Please make accommodation requests related to a disability by contacting film@gmu.edu at least one week prior to the event.\n\nIn order to increase accessibility for all audiences, all films screened in this year's Festival will have open captions (captioning featured on screen). \n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2296754
END:VEVENT
