LOCATION:Online Event
URL:https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2297231
DESCRIPTION:Learn ways to address the stigma of a mental illness and have a strategy to help someone experiencing a mental health crisis.\n\nMason's Student Health Services and the Center for the Advancement of Well-Being are pleased to offer Mental Health First Aid Training at no cost to members of the George Mason University community (faculty, staff, students, alumni). The training will be offered via Zoom.\n\nThis 8-hour training will be split into two 4-hour sessions - July 21 from 9 am until 1 pm and July 23 from 9 am until 1 pm. You must attend both sessions to earn the three-year Mental Health First Aid certification.\n\nMeeting Link: TBD\n---\nEvent Details: https://mason360.gmu.edu/rsvp?id=2297231
END:VEVENT
